animal.description:
*PLEASE NOTE:  We do not adopt out on a first-come/first-serve basis.  Applications are accepted for a dog and then a home check is scheduled.  If there are multiple applications for a dog, after all home checks are done,  the dog is adopted out to the home that is the best fit for that dog.
 
 ******Chicagoland Dog Rescue reserves the right to restrict adoption of a dog to potential adopters who live within a fifty (50) mile radius of Schaumburg, IL *****

Hello friends and my new family/person!  If you are a big dog kinda person, I am your kinda gorgeous dog!  At around 9 months, I weigh in at about  80 pounds and  still have a little more room to grow.  I am looking for a dog savvy owner/family that is kid free and cat free home  and has time to continue working on my skills.  I can be a little nervous with new people and new things at a first meeting but get over it with a little patience! I could be a good with another canine companion with some time and a slow introduction and transition to making friends. The best thing is that I will come to my new home completely potty trained, completely crate trained and looking to share some LOVE!  If you would like to meet me, please fill out a pre adoption application and a CDR volunteer will get back to you just as quick as they can!
Tail wags and kisses-Timber


**The ADOPTION FEE for this pet is $400-450.00,  which includes getting the puppy/dog up to date on rabies, distemper and bordetella vaccines, fecal test and deworming if necessary, heartworm test, spay or neuter (not including pre-surgical bloodwork) and a microchip. Free access to our weekly training classes is also included for the life of the dog, something no other rescue in the area offers.***

animal.description:
Location: New Orleans, Louisiana 

Dakota was apart of a cruelty case in North Louisiana. Cane Haven Rescue pulled her from the shelter to give her another chance at life. Dakota is approximately 2 years old, up to date on vaccinations, spayed & microchipped. 

Dakota has had quite a rough beginning to her life. When animal control seized Dakota, she had chemical burn on her entire spine area.  The burn was completely healed but she was obviously being over bred for puppies. There was another dog on the property, Dorian who had similar burns on his shoulder blades. We are confident that their previous owners were doing this torturous act on purpose. 

Dakota is house trained, kennel trained & knows her basic commands/manners. 

Interested adopters can fill out an application at canehavenrescue.com. 
Any possible questions about Dakota, please email canehavenrescue@gmail.com 

Cane Haven Rescue will transport any of their adoptable dogs to the right home. We do require adoption fees that are based on the age & health status of the adoptable dog. The adoption fee covers every single dog in CHR with vaccinations, heartworm test, deworming, microchip, spay/neuter & medications. All CHR adoptable dogs are current on their monthly  heartworm and flea medication. A CHR representative will do a home check to ensure the pets are placed in a secure and loving home. 

www.canehavenrescue.com

animal.description: "This gorgeous boy is Troy! He is an 8 year old pitbull who is just as sweet as he is adorable. He is low energy, loves snoozing on the couch or catching rays in the warmer weather outside. His favorite things are short walks, chew bones, yummy treats, car rides, and being with his humans. Troy had an awful life before coming into rescue. Due to his lack of care he has a bad heart, but is showing drastic improvements by the help of a healthy diet and heart medication. His doggie doctor said one day he may even be able to be without medicine with the improvements he's been making! He is dog and cat friendly and can share his home with other mellow, friendly animals who match his calm demeanor. His perfect home with be one with older children, a yard area to make his potty time easy, and someone who will provide him with the most love and care forever. Apply for this sweet boy today."

animal.description:
Sweet Elsa was born in November 2014. She loves to show off her cute smile! She loves to play and run around, so a secure, fenced yard is a must. She can be a good running partner but gets distracted easily by other dogs, rabbits, and squirrels. So instead, walking is a much better option. She weighs in at a muscular 78 lbs. She is very kind to everyone but she doesn't realize how strong she is. Care must be taken around very small children and the elderly so she doesn't bump into them. While she loves being loved, she is also very protective of those she lives with making her an excellent loyal dog. She generally sleeps on a dog bed but has no issue plopping down and taking a nap anywhere. She does not do well with other dogs, particularly if they are smaller than her.

Included with adoption: Age-appropriate vaccinations, up to date heart-worm preventative, heart-worm test if over 6 months, insurance for 30 days, microchip with registration, and spayed or neutered- if not already, a voucher is provided. 

If you are interested in adopting, please complete our Pre-application: https://form.jotform.us/asr628/ShortAdoptionInquiry

animal.description:
This adorable young lady loves toys and attention from her people.  She is known to get quite spunky during playtime, yet melts in your arms during a good cuddle session.  Pearl has been working very hard with her physical therapy, something she may need for the rest of her life (possibly in-home exercises with an occasional check-in with a professional/veterinarian).  

An ideal home for Pearl would be one with lots of patience and understanding.  It is also essential that Pearl continue with her weekly physical therapy until the vet discharges her.  Although she would be fine being the one and only fur-baby, Pearl has spent a lot of time with other dogs and really enjoys playing with them.  Additionally, she recently met our office cat, so it is possible, with proper introductions, Pearl would happily live with cats too.  

Won't you consider being a mother of Pearl...or father?

Adopters must live in the Los Angeles area.

animal.special_needs_notes: Pearl is a precious 2-3 year old chihuahua with special needs.  Pearl's back was so badly broken, the veterinarian that first examine Pearl said it was amazing that Pearl even survived such a severe injury...her spinal cord was essentially severed.  After months of physical therapy, Pearl is able to run around with her doggy friends but it is likely that one of her legs will never be completely normal.  She may require a back leg bootie long term for protection but it will not slow her down a bit.  Due to the paralysis, Pearl also requires bladder expression throughout the day but she can poop on her own.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Josie is currently looking for a foster or furever home! She's a beautiful girl who loves everyone she meets! Josie's ideal family/person will have a quiet, structured home with a solid routine. She'll be an eager companion for runs, hikes, daily walks & playtime in a fenced in yard. If you've ever considered trying dog agility, Josie would be up for that, too!

Miss Josie would prefer to have someone who's home more than they're away, but she's been making great progress with crate training. This sweet soul is a sensitive one; she needs your love, respect and patience in order to thrive. She's smart as a whip and eager to please; she'll gain confidence as you help her learn your daily household routine.

Josie doesn't like loud noises or chaos; she'd be happiest in a suburban or rural setting and we're recommending only older, respectful children. Josie is dog selective, so a meet and greet with any resident or frequently visiting dogs is a must! And no cats for this little lady!

If you're looking for a sweet, active girl who will enjoy cuddling on the couch as much as hiking through the woods with you, Josie could be the one for you!

** Follow Josie's journey on Instagram at @josie_ditr

*** Please note, we do not adopt out to Canada due to BSL and Border Issues

Adoption donation includes Spay/Neuter, UTD on Vaccinations, deworming, and flea treatment.

animal.description:
Cheyenne is a 1½-year-old German Shepherd/Labrador Retriever  mix. This beautiful girl was an owner surrender because they had no time for her and kept her in a pen all the time.

Cheyenne is a sweet girl. She loves to be with her people. She is good with kids and other non-aggressive dogs. She is gentle, even-tempered, goofy and playful. She has a great recall and knows to sit, and sometimes to go down, on command. She does NOT want to be left outside, but doesn't panic if you go inside for a few minutes. Meet and greets need to be supervised and if she needs to be corrected, she accepts it willingly. She does NOT appear to be aggressive but makes a lot of noise when she plays. So you might misunderstand her. If you're looking for a great companion, Cheyenne is your girl!

She is house- and crate-trained. She is heartworm positive and on treatment. She is fully vetted, spayed and microchipped.

Please visit Regard4Life Animal Rescue at Petsmart in Longview on Saturdays for more information. You can also review our adoption album at http://Regard4Life.org or email regard4life.info@gmail.com.

animal.description: Meet Saisy, who is known as 'Roo by her friends and family. She is a designer breed (boxer/chihuahua). She has the coloring, expressive eyes, small underbite, and temperament of the boxer and the small size, ears, face and 'I own the world' attitude of a chihuahua. She was born paralyzed in the hind end, and the joints in her rear legs are mis-aligned. She was left outside of a hotel and was rescued and sent to APA for treatment! Saisy's right leg had to be amputated and she cannot use my left one. However, she is very mobile with a wheelchair and by hopping. Due to the paralysis she cannot control her bowels and bladder, so she wears diapers and must be cleaned and changed several times a day. But she pays you back in spades with little loving kisses. She is a happy, active, and playful girl who enjoys a game of ball and is a champ at tug of war. But she is mostly happy just being with her person. If you have room for this sweet girl in your home and heart, she will reward you with a lifetime of loyalty, companionship and love.

animal.description: Darby is a special retired mama who is looking for her furever home. She has the most wonderful temperament, and she seems to love all people when she first meets them. She's not pushy and doesn't beg for attention, but she will politely ask for it by rolling over and showing her belly when you pass by. She's also been good around older children from toddler on up and was very sweet with all of them. While some may think that being blind would present a lot of challenges and extra work, Darby has successfully been able to create a mental map when she has been in a home, and she became so confident navigating the layout that she would gallop though the house at a faster place. When you call her name, Darby will give you the sweetest little head tilt as she tries to figure out where you are! On top of that, she has exceptional manners. As in she's absolutely perfect - she doesn't get on furniture, she's non-destructive, does great being left home alone uncrated and is fully house-trained. She also doesn't need much exercise! Darby would do best in a home as the solo dog because she loves all the attention from her humans. More than anything, Darby just wants to feel love from those around her. If you're looking for a sweet, well-mannered, low maintenance, and easy-going cutie patootie, you won't find better than our Darby. Come meet her!

animal.description:
Hmmmm, what can we say about Rosie?? She is approx between 10-12 years old. She is a Master Crumb Detector.....doesn't care to have her feets touched....pretty sensitive all over her body actually, not a fan of being brushed.....likes to rub her face on things....also prone to eating dirt if given the chance.....has some arthuritis, you might hear some crackling in her shoulders at times, and she walks a bit funny, and she's not too steady on her feet sometimes.....not sure how much she can see, maybe more than we think but who knows....most of the time she acts like she can't hear but a loud sneeze when she's sleeping proves she can.....she coughs sometimes but it's not bad....she keeps herself busy sometimes with just walking from here to there back to here over to there..m...she does play with toys sometimes and it's the cutest thing....she's pretty easy going.... if there's another dog in the house it would have to be an older, calmer dog that would just respect Rosie space. Rosie is on Galliprant, Dasuquin and a cough medicine, all of which she will need the remainder of her life. 

Our adoption process starts with our application. Once the application is approved, a member of Legacy will contact you to set up a home visit. The home visit usually last 1-1 1/2 hours and is to make sure our dog and any current dogs/cats are getting along, as well as both of us agreeing it's a fit. At this time the adoption fee is due, and begins the 2 week trial. We will check in during the 2 week trial. If it's not working, our dog is returned to the foster home and all except $100.00 {$75 if Senior} of the adoption fee is returned. At the end of the 2 week trial, you decide if you will finalize the adoption - if finalized, the Adoption Contract is signed and all medical records are turned over to you. If at any time you need to rehome the dog it contractually needs to be returned to Legacy Dog Rescue.

animal.description:
Toby Tucker is a sweet, playful 2-year-old pit bull mix (with a hint of Boston Terrier in him:) He was pulled from a GA shelter to save his life.

This 48-lb. boy loves people and loves to play, but can chill and lean on you for comfort. After a slow introduction, Toby seems to get along fine with other dogs. He is very excitable and meeting new dogs should be limited and closely supervised initially. Toby would benefit greatly from an experienced dog owner who has the time and patience to take him through obedience classes and help him gain confidence. Toby is crate-trained, potty-trained and does well on a leash. He would love to have a fenced yard to run around in, but that's not a requirement.

Toby is neutered, UTD on vaccines and microchipped. He is on the slow-kill treatment for heartworm infection, but should turn negative in about 6 months. The medication needed for this treatment comes along with him and is just a monthly application between his shoulder blades (Advantage Multi).

To find out more about Toby Tucker, call his buddy, Susie, at 706-726-2221. Toby is presently in Aiken, SC. His adoption fee is $225.00 The 1st step is always an application found at: www.bostonterriertn.org We prefer homes with pet experience and current pet history is a plus.

NOTE: Submission of an application and fee does not guarantee adoption of any specific Boston, since that particular dog may have applications pending or may not be the right match for you.

Please use the foster momma or dad's contact information above for questions.
The process always begins with an application which can be found at The Boston Terrier Rescue of East Tennessee website
Note that in most cases, we do not adopt to families with small children, e.g., 'under 6,' as a precaution to the child's safety and the dog's safety. In some cases with larger Boston mixes or other dogs, we do make exceptions. Please ask the foster momma.
We prefer to place dogs within driving distance of where they are being fostered. If someone from outside the local area is approved for adoption, they must be willing to personally drive/fly to get the dog. The East Coast division (NC/SC/VA/MD/DC) does have special transport capabilties for their kids. Ask them.
Also, submission of an application and fee does not guarantee adoption of any specific Boston since that particular dog may have applications pending or may not be the right match for you.

animal.description:
Meet Gracie - also known as the princess!  She loves attention, and even more so she loves to chase a ball!  She is approximately 10 years old, and on a diet with a few pounds to lose. She was found running the streets of Youngstown, eating cat food from a feral colony.    She can be placed with another dog, we think a calm dog would be best but she has responded well with certain dogs, all with different personalities, so it’s really up to Grace! Grace’s foster mom has been working on her barking as she is very protective of her foster home so an apartment situation would not be an option.  So far, since Grace responds well to commands she is doing nicely with barking while outside in her fenced yard with her foster mom.  When inside she’s much quieter and her foster mom is appreciative of the protection so she is not redirected.

Gracie loves her morning and evening shortish walks and enjoys meeting new people.  She has graduated from a confidence building class at Dogsmartz Unleashed and it did her a world of good.  She is a very smart girl and will need a family that will keep her mind active and challenged.  Gracie has her limits on extremely far walks and how many times she is allowed to chase her ball but is very good at games like “Find It”, Touch, Target and “Push” (the ball lol) among others. She recently learned to drop her ball in the kiddie pool and retrieve it after it floats to the other side! Self-taught   She can be a couch potato and she will chill and watch a good movie with you. It took her a few months to trust people again after her long ordeal by herself.  Now that she is more confident and secure Grace’s main priority is to be with her human. She will sleep in the kitchen quietly at night or when she is left alone but she is always so excited to be back with her person when you return.

Grace came to Legacy with extreme matting and does not like to be groomed.  Possibly from a bad experience or never being groomed at all.  She will need to be bathed and trimmed at a very experienced groomer, with patience. Her foster has worked with her and is able to trim her easily with scissors and electric trimmer. Her activity level does need monitored as she does have some arthritis that is controlled by anti-inflammatories when she is uncomfortable.

Application can be found on our website, www.ldrofohio.org.

Our adoption process starts with our application. Once the application is approved, a member of Legacy will contact you to set up a home visit. The home visit usually last 1-1 1/2 hours and is to make sure our dog and any current dogs/cats are getting along, as well as both of us agreeing it's a fit. At this time the adoption fee is due, and begins the 2 week trial. We will check in during the 2 week trial. animal.description:
Hi, my name is Fable. I lived in Conch Arizona until I came to this shelter in August 2020. The shelter manager here at this shelter saw a post on Facebook about over 30 dogs that needed to be rescued from a property in Arizona. Luckily, the shelter had some open space, and rescued 4 of us.The people who surrendered me said that people kept dumping dogs outside of their home, and they were moving, so they could no longer keep us. They did get quite a few of us spayed/neutered, but there were just too many of us to keep up with, and there was no way they could take all of us. When I first arrived here at this shelter, I was very shy and skittish. I am still pretty shy with new people, but I warm up pretty quickly if you are patient with me. I get along well with most other dogs. I have been temperament tested with cats, and I am a little scared of them, but not aggressive towards them.  I would love to find a calm and quiet home with patient people who will work with me at a pace I am comfortable with. I have never really been around small children, but I could do well with older children who can respect my space until I am comfortable with them. If you have any questions about me, or are interested in meeting me outside of my kennel, please ask staff.
                                                                              Love,
                                                                                   Fable

animal.description: Mr. Wilson has had a rough go at it. animal.description:
Daisy Duke is one tough girl! The only female found with her 4 brothers she had to learn early in life how to protect herself. She arrived to us withdrawn, scared with mutliple cuts and scratches all over her body. Months later Daisy is responding to love and attention but still mostly on her terms. She is super smart and always appears keenly aware of her surroundings. After her morning snuggles she loves to chase squirrels and hunt for lizards and frogs with her foster brother. She's an adorable tomboy that seriously loves to hunt. She also seriously loves ice cream! Like her brother Deputy she has a long body and the east/west facing chubby front paws. Her foster Dad calls them her big clown feet! Daisy's rich lush coat is such a deep black it has a brilliant shine. Her soft ears perfectly frame her feminine face and you've never seen more expressive eyes. Daisy is good with other dogs of all ages & sizes and gets along well with cats. Her experience with kids is limited due to the pandemic. https://awo.petstablished.com/pets/public/816345

Daisy and her siblings have been together since birth. They were 4.5 months old when taken into rescue. Living in the woods and surviving on their own has made them very shy around strangers. It has taken months of love, patience and a lot of understanding to build trust with their foster family. 

Daisy's foster family feels she will adjust best in a home with another dog. A family or individuals experienced with the challenges often faced when adopting a rescue dog. Middle school-High school age kids preferrred. 

Daisy has an adventourous spirit and desire to love and be loved. Also quirky, funny & animated, she will make you laugh & smile. She is a work in progress that will require an extra level of committment. She is a wonderful girl that deseves a special family,

animal.description:
Name: Monica Geller, aka Mrs. Bing
Nicknames: Monnies, Moo, Moo-Moos 
Breed: Jack Russell Terrier/Chihuahua Mix
Sex: Female
Age: ~3 Years Old
Weight: 8 lbs.
Before OMD: Surrendered to the city shelter with her brother, Ross Geller.
Best Features: Her permanent bedhead and crazy, wiry eyebrows.  
Energy Level: Chill once she's had her morning walk and breakfast.
Descriptors: Initially shy and a bit insecure, then all sass, spunk, and sweetness.  
Similarities to her namesake: Everyone's favorite, bossy, older sister. Loyal. Outspoken. Stubborn. Determined. Great appreciation for food -- even vegetables.
What makes us smile: When she’s really excited, she pants and it sounds like she's cheering “Yeah! Yeah! Yeah!” She's always, without fail, thrilled when her humans walk into the room.
Day job: Gossip Columnist. She has the inside scoop on everything happening in the neighborhood and will happily give you minute to minute updates.
Little Miss Character: Little Miss Chatterbox
What she loves most: Tie between food and her people. Followed by the giant dog beds.
Working on: Barking at various beings on walks. Not needing to have the last word with other dogs. Reigning in her excited love nibbles and kisses to feet and ankles. Just between us...also sharing her dog bed but Monica says this isn't something she's willing to work on, thank you very much. 
Dogs: Take them or leave them. Talks a lot of s**t initially but then she gets over herself.
Cats: Pass.
Kiddos: Dog-savvy kids only! She gets overwhelmed when there’s a lot of commotion and prefers gentle pets and snuggles. 
Housebroken: Sure is, but needs to be kept on a schedule including going outside as soon as her people come home -- even after 10 minutes.
Crate Trained: Yep! Has no problem going right into her crate for bed or when her family is out of the house.
Monica is spayed, vaccinated, heartworm negative, and microchipped. She’s available for adoption to residents of CT and surrounding states. If you are interested in adopting, please complete an application on our website.

animal.description:
This playful young girl with a beautiful smile is Jade, and she is eagerly waiting for her very own furever home. When Jade first came into rescue, she was diagnosed with bilateral medial patella luxation and has since received corrective surgery and has recovered nicely. Given her young age, it is believed that as Jade continues to build strength, she will continue to improve and will not be impacted in her daily activities. Despite all this, Jade has the most positive personality and is always eager for some fun times! So far, Jade has befriended all the doggie pals she has met, and gets along well with the resident felines. Perhaps due to being confined during her crate rest, Jade is not a big fan of other humans entering her property, but she is diligently learning that visitors mean more love and cuddles to go around :) Jade is hoping for a dog buddy in her furever family who can show her the way around navigating the human world. Although Jade had a rough start in life, this lovely girl is eager to bring her positive spirits to one lucky family!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed. 

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.

animal.description:
Hello
My name is Fancy. I am a 5 month old lab/GSD (Sheprador) girl who weighs about 25lbs and will be a medium size girl. I was the runt of the litter and should not be over 50lbs but the rescue folks think about 40lbs.  The nice rescue people rescued myself, siblings and mommy from a bad situation in LA. I am a sweet girl who adores snuggle time and have bursts of puppy playtime then sleep. I am kennel/crate trained and have learned to use the doggie door EVERY time to potty. I am a smart cookie who learns quickly. I am doing very well with the leash training thing. My foster mommy tells me I am a very good girl and am ready for my furever home. I do well with other doggies, large or small and all humans are great snuggle partners and perfect for puppy kisses. Are you ready for me to be your smart, loving, good girl furever?

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.If you're looking for an energetic, goofy guy to help you stay active and keep you smiling, Benny is your boy! His antics are guaranteed to make you smile & his desire to be loved will warm your heart! This good boy has mastered the army crawl and is working on his "not ready for MLB ball skills" (check out his video).

Benny is looking for a very active person to walk, hike and play with to burn off some energy; afterwards, he'll just want to hang out & be near you. He is highly treat and praise motivated! He's a quick learner and already knows some basic commands; he'll need your guidance and understanding to help him perfect his manners. Our trainer will partner with you and Benny to ensure success!

Benny is house-trained & does great in a crate; like a lot of young dogs, he has a tendency to chew things if he's bored & unsupervised. Benny currently needs to be an only pet or kept separate from resident pets; he's awkward and unsure around other dogs. No cats or small animals for this guy!

Upon meeting Benny for the first time, our volunteer told us, 'He's a great dog, he's going to make someone very happy". Could it be you? Please fill out a foster or adoption application today and let's find out!

**We do not adopt to Canada due to breed specific legislation and border restrictions**
Adoption donation includes Spay/Neuter, UTD on Vaccinations, deworming, and flea treatment.

Heath von Hermeskeil is a very handsome 7 year old German Shepherd. With age comes experience.  Heath is what dog owners dream of.  He is excited to start any adventure and ready for his day to begin.  He is happy, happy, happy.  He meets all the dogs with joy and walks nicely with them for a stroll around the neighborhood.  He pulls on leash a little with his initial excitement but quickly learns the rules of the road.  He is as handsome as he is charming, mature and easy-going, and has a phenomenal personality.  He shows affection and attention to everyone he meets. He is amazing in canine playgroups as well.  Happy is how he enters, happy is how he socializes, and happy is how his day goes.  His tail doesn’t stop wagging!  Heath wants you to know that age is just a number and he isn’t ready to retire.  He enjoys toys, walks, affection and basic commands.  He’s ready to please and start the next chapter of his life. He's a no for small dogs and cats!

animal.description:
Bo is a big, strong handsome hound with an effortless stride and commanding presence. He loves being with his brothers, sister and foster siblings. He can be very reserved and always approaches new situations with caution. Bo loves exploring the outdoors. He is fast, athletic and a joy to watch run and play. He is good with other dogs of all ages & sizes (once he gets to know them and is comfortable) and has been introduced to cats. Kid testing has been very limited due to the pandemic. 

Bo and his siblings have been together since birth. They were 4.5 months old when taken into rescue. Living in the woods and surviving on their own has made them very shy around strangers. It has taken months of love, patience and understanding to build trust with their foster family. 

Bo's foster family feels he will adjust best in a home with another dog. A family or individuals experienced with the challenges often faced when adopting a rescue dog. Middle school-High school age kids preferrred. 

Bo has a quiet spirit and gentle soul. But he is a work in progress that will require an extra level of committment. He is a wonderful boy that deseves a special family,

As he exits his kennel, Dawson’s animated demeanor can’t help but bring a smile to your face; he yearns to get out and about. On leash, Dawson just needs a little while to get into the groove but, in no time, he settles in. Once in a rhythm, Dawson meets dogs well. Still a young pup, Dawson’s forever family should continue his leash training and socialization. Because he has so much to offer and responds well to correction, Dawson’s enthusiasm may overwhelm other dogs. With his humans, Dawson can’t resist a good petting – start giving this boy a rub-down and that tail starts wagging! Dawson can’t wait to meet you, can’t wait to learn with you and can’t wait to grow with you.

animal.description:
Meet Nova! 

Nova is a stunning just 2-year-old sable. She is friendly and will greet new people warmly. She is very opinionated and will tell you exactly what she thinks! 

If you play ball with her, she will be your BFF and play for hours. She can be very high energy but will also chill out with you and watch tv. Nova loves to go for walks and car rides. 

Our girl needs to be the only dog or pet in her new home. She especially does not do well with small animals and will need a home with a fenced yard. We have exposed her to other dogs of different sizes and she is doing very well. She will walk by other dogs nicely on a leash. 

Nova has not lived with children and has not been exposed to infants or toddlers with us or her previous home so we will not place her with these families. We will consider families who have GSD experience and dog savvy kids older than 10. All applications with be considered on a case by case basis. 

Besides love, Nova needs a job! She is a working line GSD and working is the key word with Nova. She is very smart and picks up new things quickly. Her job can be anything…training, long walks and runs with her person, or playing in the backyard…she loves to be busy and will thrive. 

As we do with all our GSDs, Nova and her trainer will meet with approved adoption applicants. When a matching family is found, the family will meet with her and her trainer to review handling and obedience work prior to taking her home. Once she is settled with his new family, we will schedule follow-up training. Nova and her new family will get free training for her entire life at The K9Edge in Danvers MA. If driving distance is an issue, GSR&RC will help the adopters find an approved trainer.

Nova is spayed, up to date on vaccinations and microchipped.

If you are interested in Nova, please complete our adoption application and submit it to us. The following webpage has our application and explains our adoption process:
https://germanshepherdcenter.org/adopt

Send us your application by any one of the following methods:

By email: info@germanshepherdrescue.org
By fax: 617 249 1555
By US Mail: GSR&RC, Inc. PO Box 210 Nahant MA 01908

Meet and greets will not be scheduled unless you have applied and are considered a possible match for her. 

Please consider a donation to help with Nova’s care and training. We accept donations online on our home page:
https://germanshepherdcenter.org/

Thank you for your interest in GSR&RC…it’s all about the dogs. Please share!

animal.description:
Rocco is an older gentleman, looking for a retirement foster home. A quiet home where he can be the only animal, all adult home, with someone who wants a loyal companion who is willing to give him belly rubs. 
He is on medication for his arthritis which WJVA will be responsible in supplying. He would need carpet or area rugs in the home because he is uncomfortable walking on hard tile or wood floors.
He would benefit from having a secure fenced yard, but can still go on walks. He walks very nicely on leash and harness.  He loves riding in the car.
Rocco doesn't ask for much from the people he loves, but he does have special needs which we hope someone can give him.
He is 11 yr old, weighs 73 lb and is a Shep mix.  He needs to be the only dog in the home.  He had dog friends to walk with, but can't play with other dogs because of his legs. 

WJVA will be supply all that he needs we are only asking for someone to supply the Love and safe loving home.
Email: wjvolunteers@yahoo.com with any questions

animal.description:
Zara is pretty girl and a great dog who was picked up as a stray. Zara was very frightened at the shelter and didn’t want to be restrained, and was afraid of men. Zara has been in a foster/boarding home for two months now and the family has earned her trust, including the husband https://youtu.be/MtpwBkJD_tQ   Zara is all smiles these days. Her only issue is she does not like to be restrained, but we think with time she will trust her new owner if they stay kind and patient with her. Earn her trust, like her foster did, and of course, peanut butter! Zara is super housetrained and she does not destroy anything. Zara is about 3 years old and weighs about 57 pounds. She tested well with other dogs HOWEVER we have discovered she is VERY protective of food and toys so would be best as an only dog ?. We do stress Zara needs a dog savvy family and most of all a requires a patient owner. She is looking for a family to love her unconditionally. If you are interested in Zara please email Virginia  virginiaz3@gmail.com  When you email please be sure to add your phone number so she can call you back. We highly suggest no small children because of Zara's restraining issue. She tested heartworm negative and is current on her vaccines.

Zara has a buddy to play with, with her foster family https://youtu.be/US7NmYUj9D8   Zara is in the red collar but very protective of food and bones which caused an issue so best as an only dog.

Loves to play with rope: https://youtu.be/eThUcmg56CY 

Loves to run around in a yard and chase a ball https://youtu.be/12Zt1vfAJko

animal.description:
•German Shepherd mix,
•male,
•9 years,
•75 lbs.

Oscar would like to apply for the position of Stay At Home Dog. His skills include letting you know when someone is at the door, being an excellent recipient of butt scratches and belly rubs, sitting in the yard watching the world, and giving you lots and lots of kisses, whether you want them or not. He has a long work history of not chewing on things, and being house trained. Oscar can easily put in 9 hours of napping while you are at work, and does not require a crate like those newcomers to the field. He’s got many years experience at the position of being a good dog, and is very good at it. Oscar prefers an adult only work environment please, kids are delightful from a distance but up close can be stressful. He has never worked with cats and while he does not want to limit his employment options we believe that he would chase them with much enthusiasm. Oscar is not really a half-way kind of dog, when he commits, he commits. Oscar has lived with female dogs in the past and with slow introductions has done well playing with a few different dogs. He would likely do well living with a mellow, polite female dog up for the occasional round of chase in the yard. Fair warning – one of Oscar’s favorite hobbies is monitoring the neighborhood. The appearance of other dogs will be emphatically announced. Oscar is passionate about this hobby which is why, while he does enjoy a stroll now and then, he is not suited for a home where walks are required. We do not want to see Oscar’s hobby become his career. Oscar was placed as a puppy listed as a German Shepherd mix, and on his return 8 years later, we are thinking we might have been a bit off on his breed combo. We are wondering now if he might have some Akita, or maybe some Chow? We’re not sure, but what we can tell you is Oscar is big and fluffy and would make an excellent best friend.

Oscar’s adoption fee has been partially sponsored by a friend of Peppertree


-----------------
Due to Massachusetts State Regulations we are unable to adopt to residents of Massachusetts at this time. We apologize for any inconvenience.

** If you are interested in adopting this dog, you must first complete an adoption application at https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/PEP/Dog/. Or visit our site (http://peppertree.org/category/available-for-adoption/) and learn about other Peppertree dogs. *Note: visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

Vito brings the fun! While we can’t be sure of his DNA, we know this boy is an all American mix! 

He is about 3 years old and quite the leg leaner, independent but loves to be near his people. Vito is an energetic boy who is into playing outside and exploring. Throw him a ball and he’ll be your best friend. Vito likes to hunt around for chippies and needs a home without cats. Vito LOVES to play in our fenced yard with a tennis ball, jolly ball, squeaky ball, rope, he’s not picky. 

He does great at “trade” and is learning basic obedience. This boy will sit all day, eager to please. He does great with handling, baths and nail trimming, since his foster home went slow and earned Vito’s trust. He loves his people and will take as many head/ear scratches as he can get.

 He is crate trained, house trained and pretty good on the leash too! Vito is happy to take walks with other dogs and is polite in public. 

When it comes to play, Vito is a rough and tumble dog and his enthusiasm is too much for children and can also be a bit much for other dogs. 
Vito would be quite happy being an only dog, but we can’t rule out him enjoying a playmate that shares his same WWE philosophy. 
Based on his breed and personality, we think a female playmate may work out better than male. 

This boy is a love, looking for the right match to snuggle with and be his forever home.

animal.description:
LEARNING ABOUT LOVE:  1 year old / 37 lbs.

Hello! My name is Samine! I was very scared when I came to Mostly Mutts from animal control. However, since being in a foster home & seeing how other dogs trust & interact with people, I’ve started to trust too. I really WANT to trust & love. With the help of my trainers & foster, I am very slowly opening up to the great life that is ahead of me!

• OTHER DOGS/CATS/KIDS:  I LOVE the other dog in my foster home, I follow her lead & she is helping me to be more confident. We play hard together – a LOT!  I MUST have another playful dog in my new home. I don’t think a smaller dog would be a good fit since I’m a hard player. So, if you have a dog that matches my energy level & temperament, let’s meet / I should not live with cats or other small animals (bunnies, ferrets, etc.), as I am way too interested in them / Because I am very slow to trust & commotion of children may cause me to bolt in fear, I should not live with children. Gentle, calm teenagers who are familiar with helping a reserved dog build trust may be fine in my new home, but - of course – let’s meet!

• PERSONALITY/ENERGY LEVEL:  I have been much slower to trust men, but my foster dad understands that I just need time to trust. I’ll need a man that is willing to be patient with me, take his time, being a strong leader in a quiet, calm manner. In general, I will need a very patient & dog-savvy owner who is willing to put forth the time & effort to build my confidence & show me how wonderful a loving home can be. I recently enjoyed outings with my foster family to an outdoor restaurant & a couple of parks! I met quite a few dogs & people that I liked & was well behaved. The cars driving by fast made me a little nervous, but I stayed calm / My energy level is 6-8 when I am comfortable.  

• SKILLS/CRATE/POTTY:  I’m in the Mostly Mutts University training program where building trust in people is #1 on my list. I made great progress while in the Mostly Mutts’ prison foster training program as well as built some confidence & mastered the ‘sit’, ‘stay’, ‘come’, ‘leave it’, proper leash walking & waiting patiently to go through doors. I also ride very well in the car, although I’m still a bit nervous / In my foster home, I sleep in a crate when my foster family is gone. I love sleeping on a large dog bed in my foster’s bedroom with the other dog in the home. / My potty habits are excellent on a regular schedule. I hit a jingle bell with my nose by the door to let my foster family know when I need to go out to potty. 

• LIKES/DISLIKES:  I love going for leash walks, although I am nervous when vehicles drive by. I am still very much a puppy who loves to play. As for toys, the squeakier the better! I love the fenced yard in my foster home & will need a tall, secure fence to keep me safe. I like to counter surf, so I’ll need a bit more help with my house manners / I have likely had negative experiences with men in my past, so any man in my life will need to be very patient while I get to know them as it will take some time. New environments & loud situations take me some time to get used to.  

• MEDICAL:   I'm current on vaccinations, micro-chipped & spayed.  I’m on a medication for anxiety, just ask about that. 

I am looking for a patient, dog-savvy owner to provide stability and a loving home!  My adoption fee is $299.00. I’m located in Kennesaw, Ga.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
**We are a foster-based rescue with no facility for viewing. If interested in finding out more about Betzy, please fill out an application first at www.4luckydogs.org to start our process.***

Betzy is a sweet 8 year old female who loves to give kisses and affection. Betzy is well behaved, listens to commands and loves everyone- she especially loves her foster dad. Although Betzy has had a tough life up to this point she is a happy pup with lots of love to give. She has her spunky moments, but Betzy would do best in a home with a laid back lifestyle. Betzy would be happy in a home with an existing laid back/low energy dog or as the only pet, however she would do best in a home without cats.

Betzy's previous owners were unable or unwilling to give Betzy any medical care. Unfortunately she has been heartworm positive for many years, she has arthritis in her back hips and is missing some teeth. Betzy has done well on her slow kill heartworm treatment and we expect her to have a negative heartworm test soon. Her arthritis is managed with over the counter supplements and a $10 medication each month. Her lack of teeth do not slow her down at all and she happily smiles all day.

Betzy's adoption fee is $200 and she comes microchipped, spayed and up to date on all of her shots and vaccines. You can apply for her at www.4luckydogs.org.

animal.description:
Roscoe is a very handsome, dapper hound. He loves to play with his brothers, sister and foster siblings. He tries to be as brave as possible but always approaches new situations with caution. Roscoe loves exploring the outdoors. He is a happy, often goofy, athletic hound. His markings are very distinctive including bright "pumpkins seeds" above his sparkling eyes and absolutely adorable freckles. Roscoe is good with other dogs of all ages & sizes (once he gets to know them and is comfortable) and has been introduced to cats. He loves puppies! Kid testing has been very limited due to the pandemic. 

Roscoe and his siblings have been together since birth. They were 4.5 months old when taken into rescue. Living in the woods and surviving on their own has made them very shy around strangers. It has taken months of love, patience and understanding to build trust with their foster family. 

Roscoe's foster family feels he will adjust best in a home with another dog. A family or individuals experienced with the challenges often faced when adopting a rescue dog. Middle school-High school age kids preferrred. 

Roscoe has a tender heart and a sweet soul. But he is a work in progress that will require an extra level of committment. He just needs that special family!

animal.description:
Hello! Allow me to introduce myself. My name is Hurshi James. I believe you can say handsome, outgoing, gentle, and easy going to best describe me. I am an about 3.5 years old and very easy going. My foster parents say I am extremely smart and very protective. My little fosters say "I am funny". 

My life has been a bit hard. I was neglected and abused by my previous owner. My foster parents have been working very hard with me so I can trust men again. I am now relaxing and being myself, but only with slow introductions. It hard for me to trust not knowing you are not going to hit me again. Once I got out of the backyard and couldn't find my way home. I found a little human that looked like mine. Her dad was scared and a piece of wood to hit me. I don't understand why? I just wanted to feel safe and my little humans always hold me and want me around. My foster mom found me right away and was so angry at that man. She kept telling him "He is a Rescued Dog! He got out and just wanted to get back home!. He didn't want to hurt your child! He loves children!" Then she came up to me and I felt safe again. I am not as small as a Fluffy dog but my heart is full of love for all humans. :-(

My family is everything to me. I want all of them to be safe. I love all my foster dogs and cat siblings. I am crate trained, but can be left out all night and you will not be mad in the morning. I do not have accidents. My foster dad says I am the best foster when it comes to being housebroken. He loves me. 

I love to play fetch, go to the dog park, ride in the car, play with my foster siblings, and fetch my tennis balls. I can run around with the other foster siblings for hours. I am extremely vocal and sometimes people tell me to "Be quiet please". I just cannot help my excitement. I want to be in the action and share what I hear with all around. I also like to keep everyone aware of who is approaching. I don't want anyone hurting my human family or 4 legged. 

I am excellent on the leash and love to go for walks. My foster mom tells people to allow me time to get to know them before they come up to me to pet me. I am a "Rescue Dog in Training" she tells them all the time. LOL She is really good to me. Once I relax and know they are ok....then I cannot get enough bellyrubs and hugs from everyone. I just need time to get to know you better. Not all humans have been good to me. 

 My ideal family is one that has a 6ft privacy fence to allow me lots of room to play every day. I also need a family that is patient and can understand that time is what I need to show you how awesome I can be. I had a rough life. I need a family that is low to medium traffic around the house. A house full of people in and out wouldn't be a good fit for me. I also need you to understand my need to share everything with you via barking. I will need to have a sibling dog and you cats too. I am used to all of them. I will become their big brother in no time. 

I am currently in Houston and will have to remain here. Please enjoy my photo album with all my pictures. Feel free to share with everyone you know. I am really hoping to get adopted soon. I have been working hard and waiting for a while to get the "Green Light" my foster mom says to find my furever home. 

That's my story and my name is Hurshi! Are you my dream Humans?

Please go to www.springbranchrescue.org and complete my adoption application.

animal.description:
In April 2020 this beautiful girl was dumped with her buddy Corbin (taken by a family). The necessary protocol was done to find the owners however no one came and the finders needed a home for them to go. Thats where we come into play..

Corbin got adopted immediately but not this girl.. why? Because black dogs have a harder time finding homes? Because she os a bully? Because there was a possibility she was pregnant? Or maybe it was because she was HW + but no one would have known that. 

She is one of the most well mannered dogs ever. She is sweet, snuggly, crate trained, likely house broken but may get bored and chew the insides of her bed... she is great with my male dogs..havent yet had her with female dogs as I feel she could be a bit dominating and more of an Alpha than she leads to be seen. 

Truly a loving wonderful girl that is just a little over a year. So smart and so teachable. She does like to chase squirrels so likely no cats.

Please, before contacting us, through Petfinder, make sure you have read this bio in its entirety as the special needs is important.  Also provide a phone number to your inquiry and location. Calls and emails without using the petfinder inquiry will be required to go back and do it.  Thanks it helps to expidite the process.

animal.description:
Wesley is an adorable, snuggly, calm 5-year-old, 50 pound, neutered, Shepherd/Boxer/Terrier mix.

What Wesley needs to be happy and successful in his new home:

* Only pet
* Big yard
* Daily walks
* Gentle/positive training
* Daily medication ($50/month)
* Annual vet check up and liver panel
* Established family/homeowners
* Single story home
* Calm environment
* Older children (8+)

Wesley's ideal home is in a home with a yard (not suited for an apartment) and no cats. He enjoys a short walk a day, but is reactive to other dogs on leash so his owner will need to continue to work on training with him.  Although he lives with other dogs currently, he has shown to be selective, so might be best as an only dog.  He would be ok with respectful children over 8.


Please email right away if you would like to learn more about this dog......and visit our website www.siarescuers.org to learn more about our rescue group.   Adoption fees range from $150-$350 for dogs.  THE DOGS SHOWN ON THE SITE ARE IN FOSTERCARE - WE DO NOT HAVE A SHELTER TO VISIT.  EMAIL is the best way to reach us.We are a volunteer run, very small organization - so please be patient when waiting for a response, but feel free to check back in if you haven't heard from us in a day or so - thank you so much for considering a rescued pooch!

animal.description:
Requirements – secure fenced yard, double doors as he is a door dasher and safety is a priority with Tanner.  Applications in Chatham Kent only will be reviewed.  Children 12 yrs and older.

Tanner is a well behaved 6 yr old (est DOB 2014), 9 lb little guy who lost his home when his owner could no longer care for him.  

He is shy with new people and warms up quickly once he knows he can trust you..    

Tanner has had many changes in his life in a short period so someone with lots of patience is a must.  Once he trusts, he is your loyal little buddy.  

It was recently learned that Tanner has a 5/6 heart murmur and required a dental which was done November/20.  He was a great patient and did very well.

No cats as Tanner feels cats are there for him to chase and bark at.

This little guy can JUMP!  He has managed to find his way on top of the a table several times.  If this is something that won’t bother you, ok!  

Tanner is very smart, he loves playing with one toy in particular and can entertain himself for awhile.  He gets excited about his meal times and wants to be a bed buddy too so sleeping on the bed or under the covers with his adopter is a MUST as well.  

Once Tanner trusts you (which doesn't take long) and is comfortable, he is super cuddly and wants to be right by your side or where he knows where you are.  He would not do well being left alone for long periods of time, no apartments for this guy.  

Tanner is a pro at walking on a leash, he is amazing!  He gets along with other dogs but he prefers they are visitors and he can have his new family all to himself.  

Our goal is to find the perfect home that helps Tanner feel special as he was in his first home he was at since he was a puppy.  He wants to be someone’s special boy  and that’s our mission!

Adoption Fee: $375.00

animal.description:
Darius is such a smart boy! He knows how to sit, stay, come and leave it. He is fully crate and house trained. He loves humans of all ages. He enjoys being outside and playing in the yard. He is dog friendly but needs slow introductions to male dogs. He is one chill, easy going dude. He loves his 2 legged kiddos and the other dogs in his foster home. He is crate trained, and very good on a leash. Ultimately, Darius is a snuggly couch potato who just wants to please his "person".

Darius came from South Texas. He had wandered up into the finder's property. He was incredibly malnourished and had a breeder's tattoo on his thigh. He had fresh bite marks all over his face and lips. Friendly and starving they knew he had to be saved. They posted him as lost and no one came forward. The finder reached out to DogRRR and we jumped to the rescue. He is about 2 with heart of a puppy. He just wants love.

You can view all the adoptable pets and fill out an adoption application online on our website at http://dallasdogrrr.org.

animal.description:
Orchid| 2 years old | 48 lbs| Fostered in Trent Hills, ON

Orchids are often seen as a symbol of strength and this lovely lady definitely embodies this trait of the flower she shares her name with. Orchid came to us from Saudi Arabia, where she was found as a stray. She has had a bit of a rough start to life and has been working hard during her time at “school” - she is doing great and is ready to find her forever home. Orchid would do well in a home with another balanced dog. 

Orchid loves being around other dogs. She thrives in an environment where she can be surrounded by her friends and burn off some energy. Sometimes her energy results in an inability to focus, so proper exercise and mental stimulation are key to her success.

Orchid is not used to being around people and although her comfort level is increasing, she probably will not be the dog to snuggle up with her people. She does not show any aggression towards people or other dogs (she will occasionally give a warning growl). She has been working hard to learn her manners and has made a lot of progress, but this will probably be an ongoing challenge for her. She is learning “stay”, “lie down”, “wait”, “drop it” and how to walk on a leash. She has been spayed, microchipped, and is up to date on vaccines.

Orchid is hoping for a forever home that has some open space for her to burn her energy, preferably with other dogs to keep her company. She has her paws crossed for an understanding family who will know that she has a lot to give, even if she isn’t great at showing her affection.

animal.description:
Ducky says I'm super duper cute just like baby Yoda and looking for a wonderful family to call my forever. I'm super well behaved and have minor special needs. I love other dogs and dog friendly cats. I would do best with a backyard and a family who can let me in and out often to balance my energy and special nose breathing. I can sit, lay down, place, crate trained. He loves to snuggle up and He is a children's craniofacial ambassador. Check out his Instagram @mredducky and We cant wait to find this super sweet boy his forever family!

Meet Dallas Dog DUCKY!

Ducky is a special needs doggo due to contracting distemper as a puppy which caused long term effects on this sweet boy. This could have been easily prevented if Ducky's owners had gotten him fully vaccinated. Because of their irresponsibility, Ducky will always have difficulty maintaining balance and will be at a higher risk of having seizures. He also MUST have yearly dental care as his teeth do not have enamel.

Despite his medical needs, Ducky is the sweetest soul. He loves every living thing especially cats! Any cats in Ducky's life must be cool with a dog who wants to play. Ducky could use some help with his manners as he gets very excited to play with other dogs and when greeting people. Families with young kiddos will not be ideal for Ducky but a confident, non-reactive dog companion would be wonderful for him. This awesome guy needs a home with a fenced yard and very few stairs. He is a higher energy dog but due to the shape of his snout he should not be allowed to over exert himself and is considered a "flat nose dog when it comes to heat precautions. Ducky's forever must also keep an eye out that his tongue is not getting too dry.

Ducky is very special to his foster and to our rescue. Serious and experienced applicants only will be considered. Please email for more information. adopt@dallasdogrrr.org

animal.description:
NOTE: During the 2020-21 winter holidays, we are updating our webpage and moving the profiles of adoptable Pyrs to www.carolinapyrrescue.com. Squiggy is typical of the kind of wonderful dog we have available! We always have 15-20 Pyrs looking for furever homes, and we welcome those interested in adopting a Pyr to read our policies and fill out an application at carolinapyrrescue.com. This application is generic and to come meet the Pyrs. Those who find their match can fill out the adoption contract once they meet the right dog. We will have updated profiles featured under the OUR PYRS tab at carolinapyrrescue.com, but as our volunteers rebuild our webpage, other volunteers are continuing to place dogs, and welcome those who want to adopt to fill out an application. The miracle of rescue is that the right dog is at the rescue for the right people at the right time!

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Squiggy came to us through a shelter partner. 

He is about two years old. He is fully vaccinated and heartworm negative and will be neutered soon. 

He might be a mix as he has single dew claws. He also has unique and stunning markings – and massive paws!

Squiggy is sweet and playful. We suspect that he’s never been in a house, and while he’s learning how to walk on leash and have good manners in rescue, he will thrive with dog experienced owners who know how to set good ground rules and provide positive reinforcement of desired behaviors. 

He would be a great match with a playful large female dog. No other males! 

Squiggy is cat-aggressive. Out of an abundance of caution, we will not place him in a home with small dogs, rabbits, or any other smaller animal. 

He would be a wonderful match for a family with children but perhaps is best suited to older ones

Like all Pyrs, Squiggy needs a solid and securely fenced yard
. 
Those interested in adopting a Pyr should read our policies and fill out an application to meet the Pyrs at carolinapyrrescue.com.

animal.description: Hellooooo there!  My name is Brownie!  I am a young adult german shepherd x Australian Shepherd.  I am a distinguished guy and do best with a woman.  I am looking for a lady whom needs a secure dependable companion.  As I am that guy!  I haven't been around children so I would prefer to keep it that way.  I am particular with other dogs on whom I will allow to be friend.  I am devoted , walk easy on a leash, completely house, crate, and kennel trained.  I would like a fenced yard so I can run around as I do here at NWMNAR in the playground.  I am enjoying toys and safe dog chews.  I was on the heavy side when I first came here and have got myself back into shape and am fit as a fiddle.  I am looking for a home where I can feel safe and loved and would prefer it be with a woman.  I take a little more time with the men but it could work if you are patient with me.  Here's hoping you will check me out and perhaps find a place in your heart to make me your furever man!  Available for adoption through an approved application .

animal.description:
How fitting!?  A beautiful name for a beautiful girl!   We guess a Diamond is a girl's best friend!  

Diamond is a lab mix.   She is around 3 years old and came to us sadly after her owner passed away.  We don't know a whole lot about this precious girl.  However, we do see that Diamond has the rare trait of being able to curl her tongue!   So cute!  Diamond reportedly lived with kids for a short time but we are unsure of their ages.   Diamond has become fond of being in the presence of other pups.  She just seems to come alive and really enjoy their company!  Diamond's favorite past time is playing ball!  It must be the lab in her.  

Diamond is on maintenance medication for skin allergies and thyroid issues.   

Diamond's ideal home would be one with a physical fence and an active family to take her for walks and on the adventures that she longs to enjoy!   Some kiddos would be nice too!

UPDATE: Diamond is at Greenlin Pet Resort for training.  She is excelling in her program!

If you are interested in learning more about Diamond, please visit our website, www.crcpa.org, and complete an application.

animal.description:
Please contact Jamesa (roxysrescue@yahoo.com), 713-882-2610 for more information about this pet.Ramona is looking for love and she has so much love to give. She is a very sweet and obedient girl and really really minds her manners. She is a great houseguest. Ramona walks well on a leash and follows directions very well. Right now she is very lonely in her foster home as they are trying to keep her away from the cats and she just wants to hang out and lay around. Her energy level is low but she does like to go on walks and car rides.
If you choose this girl you will will choosing a very loyal and loving companion who will be your best buddy and follow you around. She does not have any bad habits such as chewing or digging, she really thinks she is a lap dog. She 50 lbs approximately 1 year young and very playful.
She is completely medically vetted with everything she needs, you will only need to give her monthly heartworm and flea/tick preventative and plenty of love.
Even though she loves attention and likes other and tries to play with them I'm not sure she like smaller dogs, she may see them as a cat but she is forever trying to play with the other dogs.
Ramona would make a great family pet. I will to get a video of her and more pictures of her smiling. She is calm and mellow and not a barker.
Would you give this girl a good home, she so deserves it. She does smile and acts happy bouncing around the house but everytime I get the camera she is curious about it and her face losing its smile. Her dark chocolate color is beautiful and her white chest sets it to be beautiful.
Transport across the country is available.
Thank you for looking and considering her.
ADOPTION FEE & APPLICATION REQUIRED

Roxy's K-9 Rescue does not have a shelter, all of our dogs are raised in foster homes. Each dog comes spay/neutered (fixed), rabies shots appropriate for their age, and dewormed twice. The dogs are up to date on vaccinations according to their age at the time of adoption. They are microchipped, heartworm tested and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative. ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE ADOPTION FEE.
Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.
Our organization is run by volunteers/foster parents, please be patient to give us time to respond to your emails and/or phone calls. We will reply to you. Thank you.

IN VERMONT

Meet Raven! More pictures and video to come!

Raven is 10 months old (approx. DOB 12-21-19), female, 30 lbs., vetted, is or will be spayed, and micro-chipped. Raven is in the process of starting her life over so she is very nervous after arriving to Vermont. She is incredibly fearful and will need time to decompress and learn to trust people. Her Adoption availability is currently on hold until she is ready! Right now she is too much of a flight risk that we do not yet want to move her from her foster home. We believe she will need another dog but we will need time to assess her personality once she comes out of her shell. Stay tuned for more information as Raven is a new rescue!

If you are interested in adopting Raven please fill out an Application at

www.Passion-4-Paws.org

(please make sure you have the Vermont site not CT) - thanks!

Please note Fosters have 1st option of Adoption.

Check out her Facebook page (please "Like" us while you are there)!

Disclosure:

Breed labels are often incorrect: we rarely know the genetic lineage of the dogs we rescue. Many shelters and rescues specify breeds based on appearance; however, research has shown that less than 2% of a dog's DNA determines appearance!

Passion 4 Paws does not practice the use of labels pertaining to compatibility with others or dog breed. Labels such as "dog friendly" and "child friendly" should be used with caution as they often over-simplify the personalities and behavior of dogs.

Diamond was rescued from a sad situation where she was kept in a backyard.  Animal Friends Society saved her and she is now the happiest girl. 

Diamond is now heartworm negative after having tested positive when rescued and being treated for heartworms.  She loves walks and car rides.  Diamond is great with older children and loves everyone she meets. She is dog selective, and would do best with a male dog or as an only dog where she can soak up all of her family's attention.


Diamond is spayed, microchipped, heartworm negative, and has been started on a monthly flea and heartworm preventative..

Diamond's adoption fee is $200.00.   Animal Friends Society is a small 501(c)(3) group that uses adoption fees to care for the current and future fosters in our care and to continue our mission of spaying and neutering.

For more information on Diamond, or to fill out an application, please visit animalfriendssociety@hotmail.com.

animal.description:
Abba is a 3 year old pit bull mix who is expected to be around 60 lbs. She is housetrained (winning!) and loves to hang out with her foster people! She loves to go for walks and runs. Her life goals include going on her first ever hike and getting pets from as many humans as she can. 

Though Abba is dog friendly, she has an awkward intoruduction style and a bit of a rough play style that could be interpreted as aggressive behavior by some dogs. She can be successfully introduced to tolerant dogs in a matter of only a few minutes, but she is not a good fit for a home with another dog who could become defensive. She would thrive in a home with a friendly, easy-going dog to play with and learn some manners from!

Adoption fee is $300 and includes spay/neuter, microchip, fecal/deworming, vaccines and prevention up to date. Ohio residents only.

STS is a foster-based and volunteer-run rescue. We do not have a physical location or set hours for you to meet dogs, and it does take time to answer each inquiry. All dogs are in foster homes and once an application is approved and a home visit is completed you will be able to schedule meet and greets with available dogs. We encourage interested individuals to get approved prior to searching as it helps expedite the process. A Petfinder inquiry is not a substitute for an application. For detailed information about our adoption process, including fees, please visit our website at http://www.stopthesuffering.org.

animal.description:
ATTENTION: PLEASE READ THROUGH TO SEE WHETHER YOU MEET OUR ADOPTION CRITERIA BEFORE RESPONDING. IF YOU MEET OUR CRITERIA FOR ADOPTION OF THIS DOG, PLEASE FOLLOW THE LINK TOWARD THE BOTTOM OF THE PROFILE TO COMPLETE OUR APPLICATION. THANK YOU!

Meet Alice!

Alice is a sweet, adorable, sensitive girl. She is 2.5 years old. 

Alice can get very nervous and spooky around loud or sudden noises and does best in a calm home and neighborhood. Alice would love to be a couch potato and homebody ;-). She is not meant to be a party girl!

Alice is also a bit bow-legged and doesn’t have the best knees so she isn’t going to be a marathoner or snow-shoeing companion. Just a sweet, fun, loyal housemate.

We did a DNA test so we know Alice is a Staffie/Boxer/GSD mix. Even though she isn't great at meeting new dogs while on leash, she absolutely LOVES other dogs and thrives with a confident and playful dog companion so we will only place her in a home with a securely fenced yard and a dog friend.

Adoption Process: We are not first come first served. Indigo Rescue focuses on finding good matches between dogs and families to ensure life long adoptions. We deliver all dogs to their new homes. All of our dogs are in foster homes. 

If you’re interested in meeting one of our dogs, please use the following link and complete our Adoption Application. You can either scan your completed application and email it to us at: info@indigorescue.org, or you can fax it to us at: 888-502-7660.
The link is not live, so you will need to copy and paste it into your browser: https://storage.googleapis.com/gator-users/user-680788/documents/d1742bff02e44c2ea25649cb45df5103/Pet%20Application%20Form%20December%202020.pdf
If the dog you're interested in seems compatible with your lifestyle we'll set up a time for you to meet the dog privately.
PLEASE NOTE: Indigo Rescue only adopts to homes within 30 miles of Beaverton because our volunteers deliver all of our dogs to their adoptive homes. We work very hard to create a family of our Indigo Rescue adopters because we want to be close enough to help in case there are any problems. We want everyone to be happy and successful!

**ALL of our dogs, puppies, cats, kittens and rabbits come vaccined to their age, spayed/neutered and microchipped.

Thank you for your interest in adopting and saving a life.

Sassy is looking for a forever home!

She is available for adoption through our regular adoption program or our Seniors for Seniors program.

Sassy came into the rescue in January from a local animal control where she had spent almost six years (!). Since then, she has been in an in-home program, decompressing, relaxing, and learning the fine points again of living in a home.

These days Sassy is a happy girl! Her trainers are so proud of her and so are we <3

Now it's time for her to take that next step on the road of her brand new life, and find a fantastic forever home! At about 9 years old, she is so deserving of a home where she can enjoy her golden years and love and be loved!

Sassy is cautious for a few minutes when she meets new people. She takes her cues from the humans - if you are confident, she will be your best friend within a few minutes :)

Sassy needs to be an only pet and to live in an adult home.

She is house trained, crate trained, walks well on a leash, and knows her basic - and some advanced - commands.

Sassy is a playful girl who absolutely loves toys! She would love a fenced yard where she can enjoy the outdoors in nice weather and play with her toys and her family.

She loves car rides and is well behaved in the car.

Sassy is somewhat more comfortable with women. It takes her a bit longer to warm up to men than to women.

We are looking for a family for Sassy with experience with the breed, who will work with her and Jenn and Trey to make sure the transition is a smooth one. Having spent most of her life in a shelter, she now has welcomed all of the comforts of living in a home. We are determined to set this girl up for success <3

To adopt please fill out the form at our website - https://www.furryfriendsct.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Breed:  Chihuahua
Age:  4.5 yrs.
Weight:  5 lbs.
Good with dogs:  no
Good with cats:  no
Good with kids:  no
Energy level:  unsure
Good with men/strangers:  yes
Hypoallergenic:  no

Special home requirements or medical:  no kids, no other pets; must be in a home with a secure yard or patio

Additional info:  

Blossom is an absolute love kitten and wants nothing more than to be in your lap, clap her paws together like a seal for treats, get belly rubs and cuddle with you all day long. When she first came to us, because of past trauma and abuse, she was extremely fearful and aggressive. She was scared to death of anyone coming near her. It was so hard to see such a tiny animal so afraid of everything and everyone. But after about ten days of giving her space and hand feeding her cheese (her favorite), one day she simply bounded into her foster's lap, looked up with her big brown eyes and trusted.  Ever since that day, she has been a little best friend and delightful. She is perfectly potty-trained (not one accident!), loves to lie in the sunshine outside and has just started to really explore.  She doesn't walk on a leash yet, but could learn. She's an absolute doll and despite what must have been a very traumatic past, she just wants to love and be loved. It may take time for her to warm up to her forever home, but  she is absolutely worth the wait. She'd be the perfect dog for a single person or couple who can give her the love and attention she craves and deserves. A home without other pets or children is a must.

If you are not ready to adopt just yet and would like to help in other ways, please consider clicking on the green “Sponsor Me” button above to help this dog receive the best care we can give. We rely on the generosity of others to make rescuing dogs possible.
