animal.description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Callie is a beautiful 2-year-old Great Dane. She was suffering from extreme neglect and malnourishment when she was rescued near the Texas/Mexico border. Her former owner cruelly housed Callie on a dirt lot and her only shelter from extreme Texas weather was a three-sided plywood box. Callie was tethered to a tall metal pole and she could only walk in endless circles around that pole. During violent thunder storms, Callie frequently faced death by electrocution from lightning strikes. She often was forced to drink dirty water from a 5-gallon bucket coated with slime. During the Texas summers where temperatures can exceed 100 degrees, Callie was at daily risk for heat stroke. In the winter months, Callie's malnourished body would shiver as she laid on the cold and damp dirt.
Despite her heartbreaking history, Callie thrived in her new foster home where she shown kindness for the first time in her life. She loves human companionship and interacts nicely with the other dogs in her foster home. Not surprisingly, Callie is a little needy and wants nothing more than to be near a human. Accordingly, she will need to be kenneled when left alone at home.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more.)

You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.

Her adoption fee is $300. This includes her spay surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccination, Nobivac Intra-Trac 3 vaccination, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, IDEXX SNAP 4Dx Plus Test, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.

Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.

Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Please note that a bite waiver will be required as part of Mario's adoption. 

9 year old, 22 lb Mario the Magnificent is ready, willing and able to challenge you to a masterful marathon. Test yourself against his prowess in swimming or his speed in the hundred-yard dash. 

But when his athletic endeavors are over for the day, he becomes the perfect couch potato and wants nothing more than to cuddle at your side.
Mario needs to devote himself to his people and that would best be either a single person or a dog-savvy couple who are able to deal with guarding issues. In his past life, he attached to one person in a couple and got a bit snarly with the other person. In his current foster home, that has not been an issue.

Your life will never be dull with Mario. He is unusually smart (hasn’t been tested for genius yet, but pretty close) and takes correction well. He loves to perform and is an active boy, except for when he’s cozying up with you.

Mario can become stressed easily, so we don’t want a home with children, in fact, no one younger than 18. Likewise, although he has been around other dogs for short periods, we want him in a home where he is the only (spoiled) dog. Dog parks? No way. He’s also not a candidate for walks in busy areas with lots of people and other dogs. Therefore, besides your lap, Mario’s piece of heaven is in a nice, single-family home with a fenced-in backyard in either a suburban or rural location. Even better would be one with a pool or close to swimmable water.

This active boy is totally house trained but he is not a great fan of crates. He is not fond of being locked in but if you leave the door open, he willingly finds it a secure place to curl up for a nap.

In addition to diving and swimming, Mario also loves to play fetch with his ball or a frisbee. In fact, he will fetch as long as you throw! The bottom line is that Mario is just a big mush who just wants to be someone’s best buddy. 

His foster Mom says it best:
“Mario is a really good boy. He may take a while to adjust to a new home, but with slow, careful adjustment, he is worth every second of it!”

If Mario’s craving for one on one adventure is in tune with your idea of fun, submit a S.N.O.R.T. adoption application today! Adoption Fee: $300

Please submit an adoption application on our website!  https://www.snortrescue.org/adoption-process/adoption-application/

Note: All dogs in SNORT's care are fostered in private homes by  dedicated volunteers. SNORT's adoption fee includes appropriate veterinary care, all necessary vaccines, and a spay/neuter. SNORT posts regular updates about our foster dogs on our Facebook page,  http://www.facebook.com/pages/SNORT-Short-Noses-Only-Rescue-Team/128712140542769.  Like us on Facebook for the latest news on our dogs, fundraisers, and rescue  efforts!

animal.description:
Meet Jess! Her heart is so happy when she is getting belly rubs and butt scratches. She is easy to please just spending time with her humans, but is also happy to entertain herself playing with toys. Jess has the most personality! She loves to play fetch with herself and likes to chew on Kong toys. Jess will make a great couch potato and will still get the zoomies sometimes. Jess is one our favorites because no matter what, she is happy to see you and always smiling. She was brought to us in rough condition, and she clearly has been bred over and over. Now is her time! Let's find her a furever family. Jess would prefer a home with no other animals so she can keep her humans all to herself.Please call the shelter at (706) 795-2868 to schedule a meet and greet.

Madison Oglethorpe Animal Shelter is a non-profit shelter serving over 720 square miles. We are open intake, meaning we can not turn away animals from either county we serve. Our shelter intakes double or triple it's capacity every month so it is essential we place animals quickly into adoptive homes. Since so many animals enter the shelter we often don't have enough volunteers to write an individual bio for each. Please feel free to call the shelter Wednesday-Sunday to inquire about the animal you are interested in. 706-795-2868.

Viewing and adoption hours at our shelter are Wednesday through Sunday from 12 PM to 5 PM. 
All adoption fees include age-appropriate vaccinations, flea treatment, deworming, and spay or neuter, microchip, and adoption packet. 
Fees:
Dogs over 4 months old: $100
Puppies under 4 months: $125. 
Cats and Kittens are $75 ($65 without microchip). 

For your convenience you can fill out an adoption application for any of our current residents at www.moaspets.com. Join us on Facebook at
https://www.facebook.com/moaspets. It's a great way to stay up to the minute on the furry 4 legged friends we have looking for a loving forever home. 
We are located at:
1888 Colbert Danielsville Rd 
Danielsville, GA 30633 
706-795-2868

NOTE: Our adoptions are first come first served, simply filling out an application does not mean the animal will be held for you, you must come meet the animal in person in order to be considered for adoption.
If you rent you must bring your lease or a letter from your landlord stating you may adopt.

animal.description:
This dog is new to the rescue. More information will be posted as it becomes available.
Puppies are a life-long commitment. They need time, training, vet care and healthy feeding to become good canine citizens. Don't even think of adopting a puppy unless you intend to invest the time and money and commitment required, and you can expect to lose a few good shoes along the way!

If you are interested in me, please contact us at puppies@coastalgsrsd.org or call (858) 779-9149. Don't forget to fill out our online application:  http://www.coastalgsrsd.org/webform/1774/adoption-application.

The minimum adoption donation ranges from $300 to $400. This amount only partially covers the cost of veterinary care, boarding fees, and other miscellaneous expenses involved in the temporary care and adoption of our dogs and is 100% tax deductible.

Prior to placement, all dogs will be spayed or neutered, receive current vaccinations, and are usually microchipped. If not, arrangements will be made on an individual basis. Special consideration may be given to those willing to adopt older dogs or dogs with physical problems.

Our adoption process begins with completing an application on-line. A phone screening will soon follow, and lastly a home visit will be conducted by our volunteers.

We show our dogs at adoption events every weekend! Please click on events at Events to see where we'll be next! Coastal German Shepherd Rescue of Southern California is a non-profit 501(c%293 public charity dedicated to finding loving homes for abandoned German Shepherds. Your tax deductible donations go to support these very deserving animals. Coastal was formed to serve communities in the counties of San Diego, Orange, Los Angeles and the Inland Empire. We are committed to finding loving permanent homes for the orphaned dogs in our care. Coastal is an all volunteer, no-kill, 501 (c%29 3 non profit organization.

animal.description:
I’m Blue. All I want for Christmas is a Foster or Forever Family. My human dad passed away & then my best friend, my fur brother Duke, just went to meet him in heaven. I’m currently in boarding in Lafayette, they are my family, & love me so much. They want me to have a happy ending this Christmas.

I’m a 3 Year Old Staffordshire Terrier Mix. My favorite things are to play with toys, play outside, take walks & ride shotgun every chance I get. My wish is to go to Diva Training School one day to brush up on my manners & talents or learn from my foster or family.  I’m full of unconditional love & forever big kisses to give! I can be an only child or I would love another fur sibling to make memories with.

If you can open your heart & home to me, please let Santa know. I’ve been spayed. I’m on Heartworm Prevention.

My Christmas Wish,
Blue

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our dogs are healthy, spayed/neutered, vaccinated and on heartworm preventative. They live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. Many have basic obedience skills and all have been temperament tested. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, please visit our website to complete an application: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt
(please note: app cannot be done on a mobile device)

For additional information see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

Meet amazing Al!  Al is a 5 year old 58lb, Black Mouth Curr mix. Al wants to PARTY!  Running through the tall grass, roaming the beach, going for a jog, hitting all the camp sites, that’s his thing. He’s a grab the leash, jump in the car and hit the rode kinda guy. Al didn’t have much training in his formative years, but since he has been in class he is an A student. Smart, treat motivated and eager to please, once properly trained he’s going to be a great off leash dog. Al isn’t overly found of other male dogs and probably is a little too high energy for young children, but if you are in need of a best friend and ever present wingman, he’s your guy! Al's history with cats is unknown. Al is looking for an active family or a family who can keep him busy as he is a high energy dog.  Al is currently in Portland, OR and is available for meet & greets!

If interested in adopting AL please fill out an adoption application on our website:

https://heartoftheunderdog.org/adoption-application

animal.description: Bella: 2 yrs old; Weight: 55 lbs; Activity Level: Active Companion; Breed: Border Collie/Lab; Coat: Short w Fur in Hind Quarters.  Bella is a super fun, confident, loving pup just 2 yrs old and she has wiped her past struggles and unknown life experiences away!! She was abandoned by her owner during a roommate struggle. This sweet, vibrant girl didn't know what walks in neighborhoods or trails were like-she only knew what she was given. When a dog comes jn my rescue i work on the whole dogs health, physical and teaching new life skills, this is exactly what Bella needed and we did include a little whole foods in her diet and joint support which has been a success.  She was not the confident dog she is today and knows her human partner is her coach.  Bella would do well with a dog savvy active leash partner who will continue all the progress she has achieved, who can enjoy introducing her to people and other dogs. She has good sense of which dogs are safe for her but not ready for a dog park-more meet on walks develop play dates. Bella loves people and study children 10 and up as she loves to run and show you her speed with well-mannered kisses and hugs. She will climb in your lap too and be there for your hours of need. A big yard (6 foot secure fence) is a must as well as not being alone for an 8 hour work day it’s too quiet come home and go for a game of fetch (use 2 balls please!) or a cool dog walker or work from home. She isn't the needy type to pester you-she knows humans have jobs and so do dogs. Speaking of jobs did i mention how Bella loves tricks and crates well perfect for dog classes to enrich her mind! On the leash Bella can get excited and I use positive reinforcement to redirect her, something her new coach will do for her too.  Bella is fully vaccinated, microchipped to rescue and her new partner, and on Advantage Multi. To apply for Bella you can share your lifestyle with us and if we think it’s a match we will send you an application and proceed with meets and home visits. She won’t travel without you if you’re from out of state, we would look forward to meeting you on a visit to TX. The adoption donation is $225 for Bella

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.American Pit Bull | 1.5 year old | 50 pounds | Adoption Fee $200Rosco is a 1.5 year old, 50-pound Pitbull looking for the ideal conditions in his forever home.

Rosco enjoys a long walk in the fresh powder snow. No matter whether the route is an easy green circle around the neighborhood, or a more treacherous black diamond around a park he takes on the challenge with gusto. Rosco also loves romping around for a play session with his person chasing a ball or blazing the trail by running a lap around the backyard.

After time outside Rosco will gladly snuggle up to his human on the couch. The fresh air and warm comfort lulls him to sleep. His favorite pillow is his human's lap where he will wait patiently for head scratches as he dreams of days ahead.

Rosco will need to be the sole shedder on your hill. He would thrive as an only pet in the home. Rosco finds the extra layers of interaction in an apartment building confining; therefore, he is not a candidate for apartment living. Rosco feels an unshakable chill when with men, presumably due to previous interactions prior to coming into rescue, so he is looking for a special lady to spend days outside and snuggled together on the couch.

Rosco is a sweet young pup looking for a home filled with play, and above all snuggles. Rosco knows that the forecast for the perfect forever home looks great this winter and can't wait to see what the season brings.

DUE TO A GENEROUS SPONSOR ROSCO'S ADOPTION FEE IS ONLY $200.

animal.description:
Bobbie is a handsome young German Shepherd estimated around 1 year of age. We do not know Bobbie's history prior to arriving at the shelter however we know he is eager to find a loving home of his own.

Bobbie an active and energetic young guy who believes his laughter inducing antics makes up for his lack of manners. Bobbie can be unsure when meeting new people and at times will be vocal but once he warms up he is a goofy, sweet guy. He acts like he isn't sure if new people are going to hurt him or not which paired with him being a bit shy of hands makes us think he perhaps didn't have the most kind start in life. Bobbie is working hard to overcome this though and is going to do great with more structured socialization. Bobbie can be rambunctious and loves to roughhouse with those he knows but is still learning exactly what manners and boundaries are. He is going to require patience and guidance as he figures out exactly where he fits into a household. Bobbie has not be around children and is not currently recommended for a home with children under 13 years of age.

Bobbie is currently living with other Shepherds and Shepherd mixes in his foster home and learning how to navigate social settings well. Bobbie struggles to regulate himself when the energy is high in a play group and was not doing great with the other dogs when he first arrived. He has since settled in and is learning how to play - particularly with the dogs a bit smaller than him like a Dutch Shepherd mix named Fredrick. Bobbie can be a very rough and tumble sort of player though which many of the other dogs don't appreciate. He has learned to respect those dogs when they set that boundary though and is overall doing well meeting new dogs. Bobbie is not currently recommended for a home with cats or dogs under 45 lbs.

Bobbie is a typical Shepherd 'teenager' and is looking for a home that will give him the guidance and socialization he needs as well as plenty of exercise and love. If you're the home for Bobbie please email Tierhavenrescue@gmail.com for an adoption application or visit Tierhaven.rescuegroups.org for FAQs

Precious needs your help finding the perfect family....
Precious is such a little love bug!  She is playful, happy, silly and like we said very loving.  Precious is one of those dogs that appreciates a relaxing time; when you take her on walks she looks up at you with a silly, happy go lucky look that will instantly put you in a good mood.  She is a goofball too and enjoys playing with toys and other dogs.  If you already have a dog in the home a meet and greet will be set up to determine if the dogs are a good match. Although she does well with fun easy going dogs, Precious will need a cat free home as she finds cats a bit too interesting.
Precious has had enough of shelter life and is starting to have a hard time. 
We would love to get her into a wonderful loving home looking for the cutest little girl to spoil rotten.  Sometimes Precious can be a little reserved when meeting new people but she warms up very quickly and is a really sweet dog. Because of her initial reserved nature, we do recommend any children in her forever home are respectful teens.
Precious is 2 years old and weighs only 48 pounds - she is a CUTE little gal and seriously will make a great addition to some lucky family's pack!

animal.description:
This handsome, happy boy is MOOSE....He came into a shelter in central Florida in February with two other dogs. This poor boy had lived his entire life outside, weighed down by very heavy chains. His owners did not have much and Moose went without food on several occasions, surviving the best he could off of the table scraps they brought him. Moose had a hard life and needs to learn how to simply "be a dog. He needs to learn some manners and appropriate reactions; we've been working with him and he's been doing great with us. He is high energy and can get over stimulated at times. He needs time and patience (and understanding) and someone committed to working with him and providing positive training. Because of his high energy, we recommend a home with children over the age of 10 and at this time be an only pet.
He is young, only 3-years-old, 52 pounds, and neutered. He is heartworm positive and has started his treatment, will is covered by Pet Search.
Pet Search was able to rescue this sweetheart with the help of United Paws Rescue and Pilots and Paws days before he was scheduled of euthanization ... his life matters and he deserves a chance for a better life.
Applications are available at petsearchpa.org.

animal.description: Benchi is loving towards his human companions. He is seeing impared. He did have surgery to correct his sight, but it is not 100%. He enjoys sitting on laps and being petted. He will at times play with other dogs but can also be a bit grumpy towards them especially during feeding time or nap time. He likes exploring the backyard and sunbathing. He enjoys his walks, a lot! Will pull on the leash but settles after the first 10 minutes. He is crate trained and potty trained except for the occasional marking. Because he can't see well, he can be snappish when scared so kids 14 and older are best. Like a lot of chihuahuas, Benchi can be quite the barker and will go outside and bark at what seems to be nothing. He enjoys cows' ears and lots of treats. He has gotten much better at taking his daily eye drops but can growl at times when he's had enough. Overall, he is sweet but best suited in a quiet home with no children or other dogs.

animal.description: Meet Paige! She is a black and white Terrier mix and around 2 years old. She is a sweet girl who is timid with newcomers and takes time to warm up to people. She gets along with other dogs and is fostered with cat. We think Paige would do best in a home with another dog to help her gain confidence and learn from. She is housetrained in her current foster home. This cuddly girl wants nothing more than to be up in your lap. She will need a quieter family that can continue to work on her socialization. If you are interested in meeting Paige, your first step would be to submit an adoption application on our website. If you are already approved with an adoption coach or have adopted from us before, reach out to your coach for the next steps. This information is as up to date and accurate as possible for the dog in its current environment. All dogs and puppies will need time and training to adjust to their new surroundings and to learn the rules of their new home. If you are interested in meeting one of our dogs, the first step is to complete the Adoption Form on our website at www.labsandmore.org and take some time to review our adoption process. Your adoption includes the spay or neuter, current vaccinations, microchip, and other services provided while in our care. The safety and health of our puppies is priority one, so we only allow approved applicants to meet and handle puppies. Please understand everything we do is for the dogs and conducted by our kind and generous volunteers. We rely solely on donations, and we do not profit from a dog's adoption. Labs and More is a 501(c)3 non-profit organization that operates on donations and time dedicated to this cause by volunteers. Your adoption will save the life of future dogs in need. Labs and More makes no guarantees regarding the behavior, breed, or age of the dogs in our care. Although we strive to provide necessary medical care to dogs in our care, we cannot predict future or current medical needs whether they were symptomatic or not at the time of adoption.Thank you for looking to Adopt a Labrador Retriever or other Mixed Breed Dog from California Labradors Retrievers and More Rescue. Please take a moment and go to www.labsandmore.org and click on Adopt to complete our online dog adoption application. If you have any questions email us at doginfo@labsandmore.org or call us at 858-273-5386. Thank you for looking to a rescue group to fulfill your dream of adding a new dog to your life! Dogs + Love = Family

animal.description:
Say hello to the adorable 2 year old, 47 pound fellow we call Sam. He originally came to the shelter as a lost boy in September 2019. HE waited his turn to be adopted into what he thought was his new forever home in February 2020. That new home did not turn out to be Sam's forever home.. His adopters had a new human baby and Sam did not do well with the newbie so the family decided to return him to the shelter. They did say Sam was house trained and he got along well with the small dogs in the home. The other dog his size  did not get along with Sam. Sam has been a perfect guest during his stay in the shelter. Sam is current on vaccines, neutered, heartworm tested negative and micro-chipped. You will find Sam waiting in run 850 and his ID# is 624664.

Please note, all of the pet listings on Friends of Shelter Animals for Cobb are done by volunteers, not shelter staff. If this pet came in as lost (not an owner surrender), we don't know how they might be with children, other pets, or if house trained. You can bring your pet to the shelter for a meet & greet with your potential new best friend. When calling the shelter about a cat or dog, please use THE ID NUMBER, names are oftentimes made up by volunteers. 

This pet and many others are available for adoption from the Cobb County Animal Shelter 1060 Al Bishop Dr. Marietta, GA 30008, call (770) 499-4136 for more information. Shelter hours are: Tues. - Sun. 10:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. by appointment only until further notice, CLOSED Mondays & Holidays.

animal.description:
Female Rottweiler

Spayed/Neutered: Yes

Approximate date of birth: 03/08/2016

Current weight: 79 lbs Ideal weight: 77 lbs - 80 lbs

Children: No 

Dogs: Very selective + dogs over 35 lbs 

Cats: No


Rita came to TVR as an owner surrender. Sadly, due to her owner's serious medical issues, she was not able to care for Rita anymore. Rita is very sweet and loving with her familiar friends but can be standoffish with strangers and acquaintances. Rita needs to go to a home with owners who have lots of experience with Rotties and who are able to manage her size and strength.

Occasionally she likes to play with other dogs but can be selective about her dog friends. Rita exhibits some resource-guarding behavior-especially with toys-so if she is considering a home with another dog, at least one onsite introduction will be required before she goes home.

Rita is overweight, but has lost a good amount of weight while in our care already. She has had some knee and leg discomfort that will need to be monitored and currently require some pain management. At TVR we will continue working on her weight loss goals while she's in our care and would love to see those efforts continued in her new home. We believe she will continue to feel better and better once she loses all of the excess weight, possibly eliminating the pain meds until she is older. 
Maintaining a healthy weight will be important for her longterm well-being and quality of life. We ask that Rita's adopters work with her on low impact exercises (I.e. daily walks) to get the excess weight off and to help her maintain a healthy weight.

Despite all of the sadness and turmoil Rita has endured over the last many months and recently being returned, she is still happy to see her friends. She often shows off her classic Rottie booty wiggle once she knows and trusts you. In the right home and environment we know Rita will make someone very happy!

Does Ms. Rita sound like the one for you?

animal.description:
Female Great Pyrenees-American Bulldog Mix

Spayed/Neutered: Yes

Approximate date of birth: 10/20/2017

Weight: 80 lbs

Children: 12 and older 

Dogs: Very selective 

Cats: Doesn't seem to mind


Lily is a happy girl who loves to play with her toys and explore the big fields here at the rescue. Once she gets to know you, she loves to give hugs and show affection. Lily really enjoys playing fetch (her ball toy is her favorite) and taking nice long walks with her favorite people.

In August 2020, Lily was returned to TVR due to a couple of incidents displaying aggression towards the family's other dog. Based on this incident, we think Lily would make a great companion for an experienced dog owner. Lily has also been working with the amazing trainer who comes out to TVR to work with several of our dogs. Lily has been doing wonderfully in those training sessions. We are all honestly surprised that this incident even occurred in the previous home.

Lily is sad that she didn't get along with her previous doggie roommate, but she doesn't let being returned get her down. Before she was adopted and after her return, Lily continues to play great with quite a few of the dogs at our rescue. Playtime with her best doggie friends is one of her favorite things to do. She absolutely loves rolling around in our fields with them, just having the best time!

animal.description:
SADIE WOULD LOVE TO BE IN A FOSTER HOME WHILE SHE IS WAITING TO BE ADOPTED. IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN FOSTERING OR ADOPTING SADIE, PLEASE GO TO THE MAKE A DIFFERENCE RESCUE FACEBOOK PAGE AND SEND A PRIVATE MESSAGE THAT INCLUDES YOUR PHONE NUMBER AND EMAIL ADDRESS.

Beautiful Sadie is a 1.5 yr old Retriever and Terrier mix. She is such a super sweet girl!!! Poor Sadie had a rough life before joining the rescue and is ready for the next chapter in her life. She has lots of energy!! Sadie loves to cuddle, play and go for car rides. Sadie is dog social. Unfortunately we do not know how she is with cats. Children 10 years old or older. Her forever home is required to have a totally enclosed physically PRIVACY FENCED yard (no invisible fences or tie outs). Sadie is spayed, up to date on her vaccinations, on heart worm preventative as well as house and crate trained. Sadie is looking for an active family who will share adventures with her, play and most of all love her for the rest of her life!!!

All dogs we rescue stay with us until they find their forever homes. We do not do same day adoptions. A home visit is required to ensure our dog is going to a safe environment and our dog gets along with your dog(s) and/or cat(s). We require all our dogs over the age of 1 year attend 1 obedience class (6 week session) outside the home. You must live within 1 hour of Birmingham, MI to adopt one of our dogs. No out of state or outside the U.S. adoptions or fosters. Sadie's adoption fee is $275.

Kittens: $60, Cats (1 year plus): $50, Puppies: $250, Adult Canines (1 to 6 years): $200, Seniors (7 years plus): $100 (unless otherwise specified). Adoption fees are not a tax-deductible donation as allowed by IRS regulations. Adoption fees help to offset the cost of the pet's care incurred by Coastal Pet Rescue, which are generally 2 to 3 times the adoption fee amount.
Some special circumstances may change the fee; see pet's listing for actual adoption fee.

All Coastal Pet Rescue pets are current on shots, microchipped* and spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Adopters are responsible for any shots that may be due after adoption (particularly for kittens and puppies that must have three rounds of shots to be protected).

Microchip:
CPR has implanted a microchip as part of the adoption process and the chip is included in the adoption fee. However, some chip companies require a registration fee varying from $9.99 to $19.99. The registration fees are the responsibility of the adopter and are NOT included in the CPR adoption fee. Adopters may add this cost to their adoption fee to have CPR register the chip on their behalf.

30 Days Pet Insurance: 
As a Petfinder member, all adopters are entitled to a free 30 day insurance policy through PetFirst. Coastal Pet Rescue is not responsible for this policy. Adopters must call PetFirst’s toll-free number 855-710-7387 to activate the coverage. If adopters fail to call, the policy will not be activated.

animal.description:
Kora von Korbach is a beautiful 2 year old German Shepherd mix. This dark beauty has a sweet and mellow personality with a medium energy level. She's a loving girl who craves attention from her people, being petted and calm, quiet environments. She'd love to keep you company and just hang out with you in the house (she's housebroken too!). Kora thinks that getting treats is fun and she takes them so gently from your hand, which makes training easy. Going for a walk is her favorite and she shows it with her waggy tail. She would make a great walking companion as she is easy on leash, only pulling a bit if she gets interested in something. She gets along with other mellow dogs, avoiding the high-energy ones, tho we think she may prefer being the only dog in the home. Kora does fine in playgroups that have calm and sweet dogs. She is satisfied to come in and explore around, doesn't mind the other dogs and mostly does her own thing. When she decides it’s time for a break, she lies down and relaxes. She is a “no” for cats.  Gorgeous Kora is ready to bring joy and calm to her forever home.

animal.description:
Babalu is a courtesy post for Harbor Shelter. If you are interested in fostering or adopting him, please contact Angela at the info below:
Angela Springer 
Harbor Shelter Volunteer 
310-717-2442
harborvolunteers@yahoo.com 

From Babalu himself: I've been waiting for over one year to go home. People may look at my age (11 years) and think I just want to be a couch potato.  That's not the case.  In the yard, I'm very playful.  I love to gallop to my humans & am not shy about asking for pets. I'm definitely  a "foodie" and I am very treat motivated. I love to play ball.

One of my favorite human friends at the shelter said this about me. "He is by far one of our best residents. He keeps his cubby clean.  He knows to retreat into the cubby during clean time, and he's quiet in the kennel."

Babalu is a great dog, but needs an experienced handler who is patient with decompression and time. He was anxious in his first two foster homes, but when he was brought back to the shelter, he seemed happy and ate right away. 
 
Temperament:  Easy going and happy fellow. 

Dog Experience:  On walks to the park, Babalu seems curious about other dogs & didn't show aggression.  He was dog tested at Harbor . On first dog test, Babalu ran away from very active dog. On 2nd test, he ignored the other dog & did his own thing 

Leash Skills: Babalu pulls, but takes direction well. 

Recommended Home:  Babalu would be best in a home where someone is  home full time. From his foster experiences, an experienced, confident, & patient owner who can help him with his separation anxiety is recommended. 

Training:  He is a candidate for a 6 week training program called PawsforLife K9.  If you bring me home you will get his training for FREE!

animal.description:
ATTENTION: All of our dogs are in private foster homes. We do NOT have a kennel with multiple dogs. If you find a dog you want to meet in person, please go to www.secondchancedogrescue.org and complete an application. We will make every attempt to process all applications within 3 business days of receipt.

// // Madeline (Maddie) and Tinkie are a bonded pair of super-cute pooches who finish each other's sentences and look out for each other. They are never very far apart and need a home together. Maddie is the Pomeranian and Tinkie is the Maltese-Poodle mix, and they are both approximately 10 yrs old. Maddie is about 9lbs, and Tinkie is about 13 lbs. Maddie is the talker and does typical "pom chatter", especially for meals. Tinkie is the soft-coated snuggler that will melt your heart. Both will nap in their beds if you are busy working, although they really want to be in the same room with you. They love short walks, exploring the back yard, and time on the couch for movie nights. They are good in the car and good on a leash. They are pee-pad trained, but they are not quite ready for carpet privileges, so if you have easy clean floors it will be a win-win for everyone. In their foster home, they sleep together without complaint in the family room.

The girls were surrendered to us needing long overdue vet care and professional grooming. Tinkie has gotten her dental and lost several teeth, so she is feeling so so much better and is eating with gusto again. Maddie's pre-dental bloodwork came back for Cushings, so she is settling into her new daily medication before she gets her dental and rabies. Maddie's coat and flaky skin issues are being addressed by regular professional grooming, good nutrition, and by treating the Cushings. Maddie's current "lion" haircut is a good compromise while we wait for her skin and coat to recover. Both girls get wet food for now, but can be moved to a small bites quality kibble that addresses their skin and coat once both dentals are done and their mouths heal. Although we have not seen them around kids and cats, Maddie and Tinkie have sweet and gentle temperaments that suggest they would be good with everyone in your family.

Madeline and Tinkie are loving, cuddly, come-to-life stuffies who are looking for devoted owners who will pamper and love on them. The girls are spayed and microchipped, and are being brought up to date on shots and are receiving vetting. Madeline and Tinkie's joint adoption fee is $400.

All Second Chance Dog Rescue dogs are spayed/neutered, are up to date on vaccines and have microchips prior to adoption.

Adoption fees vary depending on age of dog. Fees help Second Chance Dog Rescue cover spay/neuter costs,

vaccinations, medical treatments,

food and supplies. Please go to

www.secondchancedogrescue.org

and complete an application today!

All dogs live in private foster homes until they are adopted.

animal.description:
Name: CorneliusSuspected Breed(s): Lab mix
Gender: Male
Age: 8 years old**
Weight: ~55 lbs
Personality: Adaptable, friendly, shy, gentle, loyal, quiet, calm, snuggler, affectionate, calm, eager to please, funny, patient, goofy
Observations with Dogs: Shy and submissive, but friendly. Does well with slow introductions where he can make the first move. He gets along well with dogs that give him space and are not too high energy.
Observations with Cats: Cornelius is interested in cats, but he does not chase or play with them.
Observations with Kids: Cornelius is a little scared by the energy of children, so we are looking for a home without young children.
House Training Progress: No recent accidents
Crate Training Progress: Untested. Really loves his bed -- spends much of his day there and sleeps well through the night.
Location: DC area foster
Rescued From: Roane County, WV
Additional Information: Cornelius is the kind of buddy who enjoys very leisurely walks and doesnt mind you hitting the snooze button a few times in the morning. He is a gentleman at home doesnt bark, beg or chew on anything. He knows the words "sit" and "down" and "crossing", which is useful while out on walks. Cornelius loves spending time with his people, enjoys pets, and is very loyal: so much so that he gets nervous when he is left home alone. He would do best in a home where his people are retired or will work from home even after the pandemic. Cornelius is having a little trouble adjusting to city life and all of its bustle, so he needs a home in a quiet suburb with a fenced back yard. He is gaining confidence outside, though unexpected noises and unfamiliar people can startle him. He recovers pretty quickly and will continue on his merry way. Slow, calm introductions will warm Cornelius up to new people and get his tail wagging. Cheese and other treats are the great motivators for those walks later in the day. Cornelius is a sweet, low-key dog who will stand by you and love you without limits. Apply today to meet this heart of gold fella.
** Cornelius is available for a senior adoption fee of $250.

__________________________________

If you are interested in meeting a dog or cat, we require an adoption application. If the animal has "HAS APPLICATION" listed, they are still available to receive additional applications but also may be in the process of being adopted soon. Apply for a DOG: http://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/adoptable-dogs.html

Interested in saving more lives? Foster a dog today! Learn more, see our list of dogs needing foster, and apply, https://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/foster-a-city-dog.html

City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is a foster-based rescue in Washington, DC. We do not have a shelter. We focus on local adoptions in DC and the metro area of Maryland and Virginia. CDR&CK has a thorough adoption process in order to find the best possible fit for each of our dogs and cats (we do not operate under a first-come, first served model).

Upon accepting a new cat or dog into the organization, we provide a basic vet visit that includes necessary vaccinations, disease screenings, deworming, microchips, and spay/neuter (unless specified). We do not provide a comprehensive medical exam prior to adoption. As a result, sickness, injury, and disability may exist unbeknownst to CDR&CK. City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is not responsible for payment of any vet care, including known and unknown medical conditions once a cat or dog is adopted from us. 
Dog specific: Rabies, DHPP, Bordatella vaccines. They are tested for HW, Lyme, Ehrlichia, Anaplasmosis.

Most cats and dogs will have a house training accident in the initial days in their new home and we cannot guarantee any pet is housebroken or crate trained.

We also update our Facebook page daily with new cats and dogs.

animal.description:
Hi, Sparkie here. I am an 8 year old sprightly girl. One of my favorite things to do is to go on walks.  I love them so much that I will drag my feet when I know we are about to head back. I may be 8 years old, but that doesn’t slow me down. I can do a sturdy 4 block walk without getting too tired. I’m potty trained but being “middle aged” I sometimes have to go potty at night. If I have a doggy door I can take care of business, but if not, I’ve also been trained to use potty pads. I am very smart and pick up on words and commands quickly. 

I was at Contra Costa Animal Services prior to being rescued by MAR, and I’m now in a loving foster home. My foster mom thinks I may have never had a bed of my very own and only ever lived outside prior to coming to her. I am a very silly and goofy girl. I do live with another dog, but I like monogamous relationships, so I might prefer to be the queen of the castle. I’m a playful girl and I absolutely love it when my foster mom gets on the floor and plays with me. I like it here very much, but my mom needs to find me a loving family of my own so she can continue to save more dogs. I would really love to have my very own forever family. I’m a loyal girl, and I will love and protect you always. If you are interested in knowing more about me or meeting me in person please contact Martina Animal Rescue at martinaanimalrescue@yahoo.com.

animal.description:
Hey new family it’s me Fireball!  I’m a 50lb 1 year old neutered male.  The vet I saw in Oklahoma thought I might be a pointer mix.  Everyone I saw thought I was handsome no matter what I am.  

While I’m waiting to rescue my forever family, I’ve been hanging out with my foster family who loves me like their own. 

I’ve been going to work with my foster mom and meeting all the customers. They love saying hi to me and my foster brothers.  I’ve met new people almost every day but so far none of them needed to be rescued.  Sometimes I feel a little shy meeting men at first but we make friends quickly.  One of my new Wisconsin guy friends said he thinks I look like a Charlie.  I’ll answer to that too especially if it comes along with play time or snuggles.  

When my foster brothers and I are outside, I love to wrestle and run around.  When we play inside, I share toys and bones politely.   When it’s time to relax, I love cuddles, especially with my foster mom at bed time. 

Even though I’m all about being with my furry foster brothers, I prefer personal space while I’m eating.  I like to be able to eat out of the bowl by myself instead of sharing it the same time.  

I would love a brother or sister at my forever home if possible so they can show me around. My foster brothers have been showing me the ropes and helping me feel comfortable.

So far, I’ve learned potty goes outside, how to hop in the car, where my yard is, to come, to stay, and to go in my kennel all by myself.  I am gaining comfort in my kennel yet but I admit a nice tasty bone and some treats make it much easier to be in there.  I am working on sit and keeping four on the floor. I love my family so much I get so excited to be with them
and meet their friends, I forget to plant my butt on the floor or to stand still.  What can I say, I’m a lover, and just in time to be your Valentine!

If you would like to be considered as a potential adopter for one of our great dogs, please go to our website-?www.luckymuttsrescue.org?and submit an application. Our application process includes landlord approval and vet checks. Please make sure all of your information is current and accurate, including a valid email address and phone numbers. Inaccuracies and/or incomplete data will delay and/or cancel your application.
 We strive to process all applications in a timely manner, but with the high volume of applications we are receiving, it is taking anywhere from 1-3 weeks.  You may be contacted via email if there are concerns or questions. 
 Once all of your information is reviewed and if your application is approved, you will be notified via email.  
Submitting an application and receiving an approval does not guarantee you will be adopting the dog you applied for.  
Once you move to the meet and greet process, you will be contacted by the foster family to further discuss the dog, and answer questions you may have, and if applicable, a meet and greet will be set up at our adoption center.  
 Meet and greets are only set up with approved applicants, and we require all members in the household to be present, as well as any current dogs in the home. 
Current Adoption Fees Are:
$400+tax for puppies to 3 years old
$350+tax for ages 4-7
$250+tax for ages 8 and up
Bonded pairs vary

The adoption fee covers spay/neuter, up to date age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, general deworming, heartworm test, (if over 6  months) and a certified veterinary inspection. 
Please be aware, listed dog breeds are based on information provided and cannot be guaranteed.  
Submitting an application for a particular dog does not guarantee that you will be the applicant chosen. We receive several applications for each dog. 
Our adopters are picked based on the needs of the dog, and the home we feel with best fit based on your responses to our application, vet information and landlord requirements.  
 Approved applicants not chosen for the dog you applied for, will
be in active status for a period of six months. 
 We encourage you to watch Petfinder, Facebook and our website for upcoming dogs.  
Should you see a dog that interests you,please send us a Facebook message or an email with your approval number.  Please be patient with us, as Lucky Mutts Rescue is run strictly by volunteers and many of us work full time jobs, have families and also foster dogs. Thank you for considering Lucky Mutts Rescue for your next furry family member!

animal.description:
Ozzie von Orbis is a beautiful 3-year-old German Shepherd.  Whether it's going for a hike, a run or a swim -- yes, this boy is part sea creature -- Ozzie loves the great outdoors!  However, he's a wizard at escaping a yard, readily leaping over tall fences, so he needs a situation where he can be engaged and active, but not take off on his own to explore the world.  Ozzie is a wonderfully happy, outgoing and social boy who has been good with everyone he meets. He previously lived in a home with a child. He's housebroken and knows some commands.  Give him some pets or belly rubs to see his goofy side come out – Ozzie is quite the comedian!  He’s always ready for outings and does well around other dogs on leash (and was fine with a smaller dog in a previous home).  Ozzie so loves being outside that he’ll be eager to see the blue skies when you meet him.  If  he pulls at his leash at first, a quick correction will set this boy in line.  Ozzie is the king of his playgroups – he would love to find a furry playmate in his forever home.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Interested in adopting? See our adoption proccess.
*** Adoption Pending***

SPIKE will do anything with and for you as long as he trusts you! Spike knows basic commands, walks nicely, and will let you brush anywhere. Timid at first, he will lean in for pets and will woo, leap, and twirl when he's excited. He is very smart and extremely food motivated, so you can teach him pretty much anything. We have been working on 'sit' and 'wait' to teach him not to push through the door since he doesn't like to be left behind. Spike will play fetch with you, bringing the toy right to your hands sometimes. His favorite past time is sleeping and gnawing on bones. There have been a couple of times that he has guarded a bone (it was a rawhide that had broken off) and a rat that he had caught, but I never worried that he would bite me. He will warn you if he is not comfortable with you getting too close or guarding something (only twice in the time he has been with us), so you have to be able to read his body language and respect his space. Spike has good house manners, although has the potential to be a counter surfer. That said, all he wants to do is be with his people, so he would be perfectly content just laying at your feet and sleeping while you work. He is a playful and mischievous boy, so he definitely needs to be with an active family that knows and understands malamutes well. Spike has been in foster with another large, active dog and is doing really well, so a large play buddy would be a good thing! No cats though or other small furry creatures and in his exuberance Spike might bowl small humans over but is otherwise a very friendly boy!

Check out Spike's own foster Instagram @spiketakesahikeInterested in sponsoring? See our sponsorship information.

animal.description:
This sweetheart of a boy is 5 year-old Thor. ? He weighs approximately 65 lbs.  Thor is a happy-go-lucky dog that loves people and is very friendly.  Every morning he gets so excited to see his foster again, that he does a little zoomie dance!  Seeing this will make you want to adopt him on the spot!  This sweet love just wants to be the center of attention and he loves to go up to everyone for pets.  When he wants attention, he will come up to you and put his head under your hand, so that you will pet him.

When Thor get super excited, he does like to jump on people, so would do best in a home with older children for now.  Although Thor seems to do best when interacting with large dogs, he should still be the only dog in the home.  Since he can be territorial over his "person" (toys not so much), an experienced owner would be best to recognize and correct any resource guarding/marking issues.

Thor is currently being crate trained, which we would recommend continuing.  Although he is not destructive by nature, Thor will destroy any container that has/had food (i.e. trash cans, Tupperware).  Thor does not beg for food, but he is an opportunist.  If you leave food unattended for 5 seconds, he will devour it!  "You snooze you lose" is his motto!  He knows the command "sit" and "come."  His foster is working on "place," which he knows, but will only comply if there is a reward.  Thor’s foster is also working on "gentle" for treats.
 
Thor does excellent with baths, medicine of any kind, nail trimming and great in cars.  Short 30 minute walks are perfect for him.


Please help us get Thor into a safe, loving forever home!  If you're unable to help by adopting, sharing this post or donating is always appreciated.  Don't forget, Passion for Pitties is a 501(c)(3), so all donations are tax-deductible!…every little bit helps!
 
If you would like to adopt loving Thor, please fill out an application at www.passionforpitties.com under the “Adorable Adoptables” heading.

She does her business outside and is well mannered in the house. Bonnie loves her people so much that she can have some protective tendencies with new people coming in and out of the home, so an adult-only home is preferred and she'd love someone who can help show her that not everyone is a stranger.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Please contact Jenny Cope (giveadogahome@live.com) for more information about this pet.

GYPSY was saved from a high kill shelter in Texas where dogs have just 3 dogs to be saved and transported to the rescue in Sebec, Maine GYPSY is spayed, core vaccines, rabies, heartworm & tick disease tested negative, de-wormed, monthly preventatives and micro-chipped. She weighs around 44 pounds and is approx 2 years old.

We have no idea the exact breed of any dogs so it is up to you to look an decide what you feel the breed is and be sure you are familiar and capable to care for that breed or breed mix.

NEEDS TO BE THE ONLY DOG!

Gypsy is such a sweet girl who doesn't do too good in the kennel environment, she gets stressed and worked up. She is not good with other dogs so cannot but put in a communal area. Outside of the kennel she is a dream girl. She is happy, fun, very loving and affectionate and gentle. Of course being a rescue she does jump a little but that is just because she wants to get as much attention and love as she can.

A volunteers brings her 9 year old children over to play, socialize and walk the dogs and Gypsy is fantastic with them. The kids can easily walk her on the leash with no worries, she is very responsive and a lot of fun.

Gypsy needs a family that doesn't have other dogs and most likely not cats. she is an active girl and so an active family is very important. She needs to be able to run and burn off her energy and hiking, walks and times at the beach or lake would be perfect for her. Training is imperative for any new dog going to a new home, not only for obedience but also for trust and respect. Away from dogs Gypsy is a dream girl for any family with or without kids.

She has a little quirk in that she will try and play tug with your feet, this is something that she most likely did as a puppy and the people who owned her encouraged this behaviour instead of teaching her no. She is very responsive when told no, but if she thinks it is a game she will continue to grab at your feet. She is not attacking you, she is just playing - it will be very easy with training to teach her that this is not acceptable.

Be sure to check out the rescue website for more pictures and videos.

All dogs use dog doors to go out and do their business or to enjoy the cool, fresh weather in their dog runs or communal areas. We cannot say if a dog is house-trained, however, we expect families to understand that all dogs need a transition period and accidents could happen and training is most definitely needed.

All dogs are fed
Rachael Ray Nutrish PEAK Natural Dry Dog Food, Grain Free Western Grasslands Recipe with Bison.

Rachael Ray Nutrish Peak Dog Food receives the Dog Food Advisor's second-highest tier rating of 4.5 stars.

GYPSY is available for an adoption fee of US $550.

This fee is not negotiable and is used to cover the rescue costs of saving all of the dogs we do, the running, upkeep and maintenance of the rescue. Canadian adopters need to know that customs charge 15% taxes when entering into Canada. All that is needed to take dogs into Canada is a copy of the adoption contract (receipt) and current rabies for pups over 3 months of age.

Due to Covid restrictions, it is important Canadain families reach out to the border patrol fo rup to date factual information on re-entering Canada.

If you feel that you have the heart and home to give this precious soul a wonderful life, please go to our website, under the ADOPTION INFO tab, complete, then submit the APPLICATION. Our process takes around 2-4 days, and ensuring your references are aware that we will be calling, could speed up the process. Once you have been approved, we discuss any questions in regards to the dog you are wanting to adopt, then you complete and submit the contract, make payment and then we can work out the pick up / transport arrangements.

Please do NOT submit an application if you are not looking to take home a new best friend within the next few weeks.

https://www.giveadogahome-sanantonio.org/forms/form?formid=5838

ALL Dogs are LOCATED AT THE RESCUE IN SEBEC, MAINE. We post in various states along the east coast and Canada where we have had lots of successful adoptions to enable more exposure for these beautiful saved souls. Families will need to be prepared to travel to the rescue to meet and take home their new best friend. Sebec is located just outside the towns of Dover-Foxcroft and Milo (approx 8 miles) and approx 45 miles from Bangor. There are also lots of hotels, motels, pet friendly accommodations and wonderful camp-sites for the more adventurous families and what a great way to get to know your new best friend
.

Click here to watch a video of GYPSY. 2/1/21 8:10 AM

Roxy has the most beautiful eyes and a sparkling mahogany coat!! Roxy is a beautiful girl with a lot of love to give. When she is out of her kennel she is happiest snuggled up to a human getting all the affection she deserves. She will even offer you her paw as a request for more petting! Roxy is very strong but walks well on a leash once she’s calmed down from the excitement of getting out for a walk. She loves her toys and is very strong chewer so will need some durable toys to play with! Just check out her video playing in our Puppy Playground. You can see what a fun loving pup she is and what a $10 baby pool can do to make her so happy!
Unfortunately shelter life has been very stressful for Roxy.  She desperately needs to find a home that will understand that she may have some anxiety. All she needs is the right people to help her to relax, decompress, and learn what it feels like to be part of a family. We know that her person is out there so please share and help us find her her forever home.
Roxy loves sunbathing. long soaks in the pool,  giving only slightly sloppy puppy kisses and of course her most favorite pastime is snuggling in close while you tell her just how pretty she is!! Roxy prefers not to have to share her home with other animals or young children - she is very much a princess and would like all of your attention alllll of the time please!! 

Roxy has NO ADOPTION FEE.

animal.description:
This very cute Pyrenees mix boy is Everest - a young and very sweet boy. Everest came to rescue from a family who wanted him to guard livestock but they did not keep him fenced and ignored him. Everest liked to go wandering and visiting all of the neighboring people, farms and dogs as he is a social, friendly boy. Everest liked to chase cows to try and play with them, which was not appreciated. Everest is great with people and even does well with strangers. He would love to be your new best friend. He is a sweet guy, does great with other dogs, is fine with cats, too and also likes kids. Everest is such a nice boy - everybody that meets him just loves him, and so will you. He is smart and learns well so he should really enjoy being able to live inside for a change. He is currently in boarding and just waiting for a home or foster home to go to. Everest would love a family of his own with a fenced in yard and a dog pal to play with!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
NGPR dogs are in foster homes throughout the U.S., NOT Beacon, NY. View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed.

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.

animal.description:
Jazzy is looking for a home !

She is available for adoption through our regular adoption program or our Seniors for Seniors program

Jazzy came to us from a local animal control facility where she had spent many years. She has spent with Jenn Ct and Trey and has done amazing :) - and is now ready to find a totally terrific home.

She is a pit bull, about 9 years old. Jazzy is a well-mannered girl. She is house trained, crate trained, walks well on a leash, and knows all of her basic commands.

Jazzy has done well with certain male dogs but is dog selective and we need her to go to an only-pet home as a result.

She needs an adult home with people experienced with the breed.

She is a cuddle-bug, loves car rides, and loves playing outside in the nice weather with her toys.

Her favorite time of all is treat or dinner time!

Jazzy likes most people - if she is not a fan of a particular person, she will let you know.

She will sometimes get excited and jump up. However she takes corrections well.

So ... if you love blue pit bulls and have experience with the breed - and if you can be a firm leader - then our Jazzy is your girl :)

She is a wonderful (and absolutely gorgeous) dog who is 1000% deserving of a family who will love her (and spoil her a little bit) forever and ever.

To adopt (or foster-to-adopt) please fill out the form at our website - https://www.furryfriendsct.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Bob the very handsome freckled faced Great Pyrenees is a 1 year young guy who is an owner surrender due to no fault of his own. Bob is house trained, walks well on a leash and is crate trained but he isn't trustworthy with free roam of the house yet. He will of course bark to alert, he might dig when bored and still has some puppy chewing but with the right amount of exercise, stimulation and supervision (as all puppies require) Bob will learn daily and he matures. He has been allowed on the furniture, is good in the car and has lived with another dog and cat previously. Bob prefers submissive siblings and more mellow dogs who don't get in his face. He can be a bit shy with new people but he warms up quickly and then loves to be petted. He loves to be with his people, he will come when called, he is sweet, loving and likes to snuggle and sleep at your feet. Need a shadow? Bob is your man!! He will need some patience to help him through his shy phase and he learns to be a bit more confident. Bob loves any kind of toy and chew bones and is more than happy to chew on either!

Giant Breed Experienced Homes Only.

To see the most up to date adoption status of this dog, please visit www.bigdogshugepaws.com
This is just one of hundreds of gentle giants available for adoption at BDHPI! It is best not to get your heart set on any one particular dog upfront because there is no guarantee they will still be available once you are approved or that they are even the right match for your family. Purebred puppies are only eligible for adoption to giant breed experienced homes.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Bender and Darling are very bonded. A perfect home for them would be a nice quiet home with a fenced in yard. Bender is leary at first when meeting people where Darling will go right up to people. Bender needs an owner where his leariness is accepted and his owner is able to work with him and reassure all is well.

Bender is a sweet boy, and is very gentle and loving with others. He is a bit shy when first meeting people, but warms up quickly. He absolutely loves being outside and playing with other dogs.

Dog 4 a Day Update :

We took Bender and Darling to Lake Eola to participate in the dog for a day program. They did great! They walk great and even better when they are together. They did not demonstrate any aggressive behavior towards dogs or humans and they let other humans pet them. We had a wonderful day and we were able to bring my dog and other two dogs with us and they all got along well.

Bender and Darling have become very bonded. They are both a bit shy upon meeting but come around quickly and are very friendly and playful. They both love going to the dog park. They do so well together and we feel that if they were separated, they would be very upset.

Dog 4 A Day Update: Bender is such a sweetheart!! He was really well-behaved and mellow all day. We had no problems walking him on the leash. He stayed close to me or went a little ahead to explore most of the time. He was interested in the other dogs at the park and was friendly with all of them. He liked being around children and let them pet him. We went to get food and he was happy to lay down and hang out on the patio with us while we ate. Every time we were in the car he just quietly curled up in the back seat and fell asleep or looked out the window. Overall, he's a very sweet, relaxed dog. If I could have a dog where I lived I would adopt him in a heartbeat! He just needs a loving home!

animal.description:
Meet Winslow! He's a 3 yo, 13lb Jack Russell Terrier Mix. Winslow came into foster care early July knowing he was going to be a "special case".  When he was pulled from the shelter he was "odd eyed", at the time we didn't know if that meant he just had 2 different colored eyes or if there was something more going on.  Once we had him in foster care and seen by one of our vets it was verified that Winslow was blind and suffered trauma to his right eye and that it needed to be removed.  To date he has had the eye removed and is doing great!  He also has a stunted right front leg that’s congenital that gives him no trouble, he walks, runs and plays on it just fine, from the looks of it you'd never really know there is any wrong just a slight bow, all that is required of that is a daily joint supplement. 

Winslow is dog and cat friendly.  Due to some mild resource guarding at times, I would recommend that he be placed in a home with older kids.  Winslow is very social especially with other dogs but not with other excitable, “in your face” dogs.  His ideal home would have a fenced in yard, again the JRT breed and mixes are known for their tendency to run, dig and excitable nature so they cannot be off leash, he loves to sprint around the yard and will look for areas to escape if given the opportunity, you will need to keep an eye on this little Houdini! He loves to go for car rides and loves his daily walks.    

Winslow is potty trained, knows basic commands (come, sit, no, off) but he can also be very stubborn and likes to challenge you so a home that has experience with behavioral issues is preferred. He does not like to be crated, he has shown some mild separation anxiety so he would prefer to be out roaming the house, hanging with his people or sleeping under blankets if you let him, he also loves to snuggle under the covers when its bedtime.  Winslow has come a long way since entering into foster care.  From day one he didn’t know how to play with toys or even properly play with his other foster siblings, it took him 6 weeks even to give kisses but with patience and love he’s come around.  

Winslow has developed into a very sweet and super affectionate little guy looking for the right home to share all the love he has to give, once you earn his trust he will forever be by your side, are you his match?

animal.description:
Look, I know I'm cute, but I am so much more than just this handsome face. My name is Monroe. I am a 2 year old, 40 pound Australian Shepherd/Border Collie mix, and I am looking for an extra special home to call my own. I am a nervous, old fashioned kind of guy, so I need multiple dates with someone before we can discuss moving in together. Speaking of forever, my forever home will need a fully privacy fenced yard, so no apartments for me please. I am too nervous to share my home with human children, but I love cats and other dogs. In fact, I need another dog friend in my home in order to help me settle in. You see, I have missed out on a lot of experiences in my first two years of life, so I need someone committed to helping me explore the world while I get used to new people and places, and learn what it means to enjoy being a dog. Once I trust you, I am a sweet and goofy boy, but I am looking for someone who will be patient with me as we learn that trust together. I do also struggle with separation anxiety at the moment; I am working hard to overcome my fears, but would currently do best in a home where I will be alone very little. If you think we could be a match made in heaven, then fill out that adoption application so we can start working toward our forever. 

My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

GAINESVILLE, TEXAS

AVAILABLE FOR: FOSTER, FOSTER-TO-ADOPT OR ADOPTION

Meet Zoey!  She is a beautiful little tripawd Anatolian Shepherd or mix.  Zoey came into the shelter as a stray so we have no background on her.  She is spayed, fully vaccinated and is heartworm negative. Estimated DOB March/2019.

The shelter vet though her missing leg may have been a birth defect and not an amputation but we will likely never know how she ended up being a three legged girl.  But...  SHHHHH don't say it too loudly because Zoey is not aware that she is different from other dogs or is missing a leg.  She is a pistol!  She can run like the wind and is a very energetic pup!

Zoey is in the boarding kennel right now and we are looking for either a foster or adoption for her.

She is very friendly with people, good with other dogs and seems to be good with kitties. She's going to need some work on basic commands and such but she is very smart and very trainable.

Please email us for more information asdrescue@gmail.com

Transport: **PLEASE READ CAREFULLY**

***If you are within 1,000 miles, we can usually help with transport using volunteer drivers (depending on the route/availability of volunteers).

***If you live farther than 1,000 miles, we can still assist, however, the adopting party will need to drive any mileage over 1,000 miles.  For example, if you live 1200 miles away, you would have to drive 200 miles out.

Whoever is lucky enough to have this sweet boy I do hope you’ll contact me with a photo and how he is doing in his new home.

animal.description: KaLeu (pronounced "Ka-Loy", German for Captain-Lieutenant) is a super-sweet German Shepherd Dog.  He is also a super shy dog.  Once he gets to know someone, and is comfortable with that person, his favorite thing is to be right next to that person.  However, it takes him a little while to warm up to someone.  If he is scared, he looks for somewhere to hide, and tries to make himself as small as possible.  KaLeu prefers other dogs to humans. His favorite activity is playing chase with another dog, and his second favorite activity is carrying toys around. KaLeu has a delicate digestive system, which is intolerant to many foods. Thus, he needs to be on a special diet, which is more expensive than regular dog food.  KaLeu is looking for a forever home with someone what will give him lots of love, and keep him close.  Because it takes KaLeu a little while to warm up to someone, he will take time to bond with his new owner.  Thus, he is looking for a forever home within a 50-mile radius of Goleta, CA.  That way, he can visit with his new owner several times to bond with that person, before moving into his forever home.  Adoption fee is $100.  Donations are always welcome.
